307/1523201|jstor=1523201 }}\n* {{citation |last=Sung |first=Tz'u |others=translated by Brian E. McKnight |chapter= |title = The Washing Away of Wrongs: Forensic Medicine in Thirteenth-Century China |year=1981 |publisher=[[University of Michigan Press]] |location=Ann Arbor |isbn = 978-0-89264-800-9 }}\n* {{citation |title=Expansion and Contraction Patterns of Large Polities: Context for Russia |first=Rein |last=Taagepera |author-link=Rein Taagepera |journal=[[International Studies Quarterly]] |year=1997 |volume=41 |issue=3 |pages=475\u2013504 |doi=10.1111/0020-8833.00053 |jstor=2600793|url=http://www.escholarship.org/uc/item/3cn68807 }}\n* {{citation |last=Temple |first=Robert |others=with a foreword by Joseph Needham |title = The Genius of China: 3,000 Years of Science, Discovery, and Invention |year=1986 |publisher=Simon and Schuster |location=New York |isbn = 978-0-671-62028-8 }}\n* {{citation |last=Veeck |first=Gregory |last2=Pannell |first2=Clifton W. |last3=Smith |first3=Christopher J. |last4=Huang |first4=Youqin |title=China's Geography: Globalization and the Dynamics of Political, Economic, and Social Change |year=2007 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield Publishers |location=Lanham |isbn=978-0-7425-5402-3 |url=https://archive.org/details/chinasgeographyg0000veec }}\n* {{citation |last=Wagner |first=Donald B. |year=2001 |title = The Administration of the Iron Industry in Eleventh-Century China |journal=Journal of the Economic and Social History of the Orient |volume = 44 |issue = 2 |pages = 175\u2013197 |url = |doi = 10.1163/156852001753731033 }}\n* {{citation |last=Wang |first=Lianmao |title = Return to the City of Light: Quanzhou, an eastern city shining with the splendour of medieval culture |year=2000 |publisher = Fujian People's Publishing House |location= |isbn = |pages= |url = }}\n* {{Citation |last=West |first=Stephen H. |year=1997 |title = Playing With Food: Performance, Food, and The Aesthetics of Artificiality in The Sung and Yuan |journal = Harvard Journal of Asiatic Studies |volume=57 |issue=1 |pages = 67\u2013106 |doi = 10.2307/2719361 |jstor = 2719361 }}\n* {{citation |last=Wright |first=Arthur F. |title = Buddhism in Chinese History |year=1959 |publisher=[[Stanford University Press]] |location=Stanford |isbn = |pages= |url = }}\n* {{citation |last1=Yen-Mah |first1=Adeline |title=China; Land of Dragon and Emperors |date=2008 |publisher=Random House, Inc. |location=New York |isbn=978-0-385-73748-7 |url=https://archive.org/details/chinalandofdrago00maha }}\n* {{citation |last=Yuan |first=Zheng |year=1994 |title = Local Government Schools in Sung China: A Reassessment |journal = History of Education Quarterly |volume=34 |issue=2 |pages=193\u2013213 |doi = 10.2307/369121 |jstor = 369121 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{Library resources box}}{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |title = \"This Culture of Ours\": Intellectual Transitions in T'ang and Sung China |last = Bol |first = Peter K. |publisher = Stanford University Press|year = 1992 |isbn = 978-0-8047-1920-9 |location = Stanford, CA |ref = none }}\n* {{Citation |last=Cotterell |first=Arthur |title = The Imperial Capitals of China \u2013 An Inside View of the Celestial Empire |year=2007 |ref = none |location=London |publisher=Pimlico |isbn = 978-1-84595-009-5 }}\n* {{Citation |last=Gascoigne |first=Bamber |title = The Dynasties of China: A History |year=2003 |ref = none |location=New York |publisher=Carroll & Graf |isbn = 978-1-84119-791-3 }}\n* {{Citation |last=Gernet |first=Jacques |title = A history of Chinese civilization |year=1982 |ref = none |location=Cambridge |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn = 978-0-521-24130-4 }}\n* {{Citation |last=Kruger |first=Rayne |title=All Under Heaven: A Complete History of China |year=2003 |ref=none |location=Chichester |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |isbn=978-0-470-86533-0 |url=https://archive.org/details/allunderheavenco0000krug }}\n* {{cite book |title = The Age of Confucian Rule: The Song Transformation of C