er-1202189729/ |archive-date=December 18, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Reimann |first=Tom |title='The Mandalorian': Werner Herzog Calls the Series \"Cinema Back At Its Best\" |work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |date=November 14, 2019 |url=https://collider.com/the-mandalorian-werner-herzog-cinema/ |accessdate=January 26, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200109124826/https://collider.com/the-mandalorian-werner-herzog-cinema/ |archive-date=January 9, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Herzog strongly urged the show's filmmakers to use puppetry for the Child character and not computer-generated imagery, calling them \"cowards\" for considering using CGI in its place.<ref name=\"Couch1115\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Husband |first=Andrew |title=When 'The Mandalorian' Considered Replacing Baby Yoda's Puppet With CGI, Werner Herzog Rebuked Them |work=[[Uproxx]] |date=November 26, 2019 |url=https://uproxx.com/tv/werner-herzog-baby-yoda-cowards/ |accessdate=January 27, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127044708/https://uproxx.com/tv/werner-herzog-baby-yoda-cowards/ |archive-date=January 27, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Lavin |first=Will |title=Werner Herzog called out 'Mandalorian' crew for almost replacing Baby Yoda puppet with CGI: \"You are cowards\" |work=[[NME]] |date=November 27, 2019 |url=https://www.nme.com/news/tv/werner-herzog-mandalorian-baby-yoda-puppet-cgi-you-are-cowards-2579577 |accessdate=January 27, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191129021143/https://www.nme.com/news/tv/werner-herzog-mandalorian-baby-yoda-puppet-cgi-you-are-cowards-2579577 |archive-date=November 29, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The Client character and Herzog's performance have received generally positive reviews from critics.<ref name=\"Anderton0507\" /><ref name=\"Venable1218\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Serba |first=John |title=Why Werner Herzog's Participation in 'The Mandalorian' is a Monumental Casting Coup |work=[[New York Post|Decider.com]] |date=November 14, 2019 |url=https://decider.com/2019/11/14/werner-herzog-the-mandalorian/ |accessdate=January 27, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191217073250/https://decider.com/2019/11/14/werner-herzog-the-mandalorian/ |archive-date=December 17, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Dr. Pershing===\n[[Image:Omid Abtahi by Gage Skidmore.jpg|thumb|upright|alt=A smiling man with black hair and facial hear, wearing eyeglasses and a green lanyard, speaks into a microphone.|Dr. Pershing is portrayed by Omid Abtahi.]]\nDr. Pershing is a doctor and scientist affiliated with the Imperial remnant who works with the Client in his attempts to capture the Child.<ref name=\"Renfro1112\">{{cite news |last=Renfro |first=Kim |title=The opening episode of Disney Plus' 'The Mandalorian' ends on a surprising cliffhanger. Here's what you need to know. |work=[[Insider Inc.#Insider|Insider]] |date=November 12, 2019 |url=https://www.insider.com/mandalorian-first-episode-ending-meaning-star-wars-2019-11 |accessdate=February 11, 2020}}</ref> He has appeared in two episodes of ''The Mandalorian'',<ref>{{cite news |last=Kain |first=Erik |title='The Mandalorian' Episode 6 Recap And Review: 'The Prisoner' Is More 'Star Wars' Gold |work=[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]] |date=December 13, 2019 |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2019/12/13/the-mandalorian-episode-6-recap-and-review-the-prisoner-is-more-star-wars-gold/#51c84ab644d9 |accessdate=February 11, 2020}}</ref> starting with the series premiere \"[[Chapter 1: The Mandalorian]]\", in which he is present on an Imperial compound on Nevarro when the Client hires the Mandalorian to track down and deliver the Child.<ref name=\"Renfro1112\" /><ref name=\"Breznican0414\">{{cite news |last=Breznican |first=Anthony |author-link=Anthony Breznican |title=Here's what happened in the secret footage of ''The Mandalorian'' |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=April 14, 2019 |url=https://ew.com/tv/2019/04/14/secret-footage-the-mandalorian/ |accessdate=February 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416053035/https://ew.com/tv/2019/04/14/secret-footage-the-mandalorian/ |archive-date=April 16, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Rife |first=Katie |title=Jon Favreau unveils footage from The Mandalorian at Star Wars Celebration |work=[[The A.V. Club]] |date=April 14, 2019 |url=https://news.avclub.com/jon-favreau-unveils-footage-from-the-mandalorian-at-sta-1834032622 |accessdate=February 11, 2020}}</ref> When the Client says he is willing to pay half-price for proof of termination,<ref name=\"Renfro1112\" /><ref name=\"Bundel1127\">{{cite news |last=Bundel |first=Ani |title=This 'Mandalorian' Theory About Baby Yoda Is So Important |work=[[Elite Daily]] |date=November 27, 2019 |url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/this-mandalorian-theory-about-baby-yoda-is-so-important-19409245 |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Ciacoya1113\">{{cite news |last=Ciacoya |first=Ben |title=The Mandalorian Hints at the Return of Kamino Cloning |work=[[Comic Book Resources]] |date=November 13, 2019 |url=https://www.cbr.com/the-mandalorian-hints-at-the-return-of-kamino-cloning/ |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref> Pershing objects and says the child should be delivered alive.<ref name=\"Renfro1112\" /><ref name=\"Ciacoya1113\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Renfro |first=Kim |title=A quick guide to every 'Mandalorian' character you should know |work=[[Insider Inc.#Insider]] |date=November 13, 2019 |url=https://www.insider.com/mandalorian-character-names-actors-2019-11 |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref> Pershing appears again in \"Chapter 3: The Sin\", when the Mandalorian delivers the Child to the Client.<ref name=\"Miller1122\">{{cite news |last=Miller |first=Matt |title=''The Mandalorian'' Episode Three Confirms a Theory About Why Baby Yoda Is So Important |work=[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]] |date=November 22, 2019 |url=https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/tv/a29890022/the-mandalorian-episode-3-baby-yoda-clone-theory/ |accessdate=February 11, 2020}}</ref> Later, when discussing the Child, the Client orders Pershing to \"extract the necessary material and be done with it\", but Pershing again protests, noting their employer has explicitly ordered them to bring the Child back alive.<ref name=\"Venable1218\">{{cite news |last=Venable |first=Nick |title=The Mandalorian: 6 Biggest Questions After Episode 7 |work=CinemaBlend |date=December 18, 2019 |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/television/2487029/the-mandalorian-6-biggest-questions-after-episode-7 |accessdate=January 28, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125162225/https://www.cinemablend.com/television/2487029/the-mandalorian-6-biggest-questions-after-episode-7 |archive-date=January 25, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Miller1122\" /><ref name=\"Smail1125\">{{cite news |last=Smail |first=Gretchen |title=Is Baby Yoda A Clone? 'The Mandalorian' Gave Fans Another Tiny Hint |work=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]] |date=November 25, 2019 |url=https://www.bustle.com/p/is-baby-yoda-a-clone-the-mandalorian-gave-fans-another-tiny-hint-19381972 |accessdate=February 11, 2020}}</ref> The Mandalorian later returns to the Imperial compound to rescue the child, killing all the stormtroopers there and finding Pershing with the Child, who is sedated and strapped into laboratory equipment. When the Mandalorian threatens Pershing, the scientist pleads for mercy and insists he protected the Child and prevented him from being killed.<ref name=\"Bundel1127\" /> The Mandalorian takes the Child and leaves Pershing unharmed.<ref name=\"Snowden1122\"/>\n\nPershing is portrayed by [[Omid Abtahi]],<ref name=\"Chapman1118\" /> who previously voiced a Mandalorian character named Amis in the animated series ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars (2008 TV series)|Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]''.<ref>{{cite news |last=Snowden |first=Scott |title='The Mandalorian': Here's What We Know So Far About the 'Star Wars' Live Action Show |work=[[Space.com]] |date=May 2, 2019 |url=https://www.space.com/star-wars-the-mandalorian-what-we-know.html |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref> Pershing's costume includes a patch on his right arm with an insignia similar to one worn by [[Human cloning|clones]] in the cloning facility on the planet [[List of Star Wars planets and moons#Kamino|Kamino]] in the [[Star Wars prequel trilogy|prequel]] film ''[[Star Wars: Episode II \u2013 Attack of the Clones]]''.<ref name=\"Smail1125\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Trivedi |first=Sachin |title='The Mandalorian' Spoilers: Why Dr. Pershing Wants That Baby |work=[[International Business Times]] |date=November 18, 2019 |url=https://www.ibtimes.com/mandalorian-spoilers-why-dr-pershing-wants-baby-2868211 |accessdate=February 11, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Dumaraog |first=Ana |title=Star Wars Theory: The Mandalorian's [Spoiler] Is A Clone |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=November 17, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/star-wars-mandalorian-baby-yoda-clone/ |accessdate=February 11, 2020}}</ref> This has led to speculation among some fans and writers that Pershing's plans for the Child involve cloning.<ref name=\"Miller1122\" /><ref name=\"Chapman1118\">{{cite news |last=Chapman |first=Tom |title=This Mandalorian theory could have huge consequences for Star Wars canon |work=[[Digital Spy]] |date=November 18, 2019 |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/ustv/a29829812/mandalorian-yoda-clone/ |accessdate=February 11, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Goslin |first=Austen |title=A Star Wars Easter egg may reveal The Mandalorian's endgame for Baby Yoda |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |date=November 23, 2019 |url=https://www.polygon.com/star-wars/2019/11/23/20978396/mandalorian-easter-egg-baby-yoda-kamino-symbol-attack-of-the-clones |accessdate=February 11, 2020}}</ref> Pershing also wears [[glasses]], making him the first human live-action character in Disney's ''Star Wars'' canon to do so. This was contrary to a rule ''Star Wars'' creator [[George Lucas]] imposed, before selling the franchise to Disney, that no character wear glasses in the ''Star Wars'' universe.<ref>{{cite news |last=Jones |first=Camden |title=The Mandalorian Breaks One Of George Lucas' Original Star Wars Rules |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=January 12, 2020 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-george-lucas-rules-glasses-doctor-pershing/ |accessdate=February 11, 2020}}</ref> Pershing's costume, which also included a grey shirt with white shoulders and a high collar, was ranked eighth on a ''[[Screen Rant]]'' list of the ten best costumes in the first season of ''The Mandalorian''.<ref name=\"Atkin0108\">{{cite news |last=Atkin |first=Jessie |title=The Mandalorian: 10 of the Best Outfits From Season 1 |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=January 8, 2020 |url=https://screenrant.com/star-wars-mandalorian-best-fashion-disney-plus/ |accessdate=February 11, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200109140807/https://screenrant.com/star-wars-mandalorian-best-fashion-disney-plus/ |archive-date=January 9, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Inverse]]'' writer Allie Gemmill called Dr. Pershing an interesting character, particularly due to the mystery behind his possible association with Kamino.<ref>{{cite news |last=Gemmill |first=Allie |title=7 questions 'The Mandalorian' still needs to answer in season 2 |work=[[Inverse (website)|Inverse]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url= https://www.inverse.com/article/62017-mandalorian-season-2-release-date-answer-7-questions-baby-yoda-origins-home-planet |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===The Armorer===\n{{Main|The Armorer}}\nThe Armorer is the leader of a tribe of Mandalorian warriors on Nevarro, which includes the show's title character. She provides spiritual guidance for the clan, and forges and repairs their armor,<ref name=\"Breznican1122-a\">{{cite news |last=Breznican |first=Anthony |author-link=Anthony Breznican |title=The Armorer: Unmasking ''The Mandalorian''{{'}}s Mysterious Blacksmith |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |date=November 22, 2019 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/11/the-armorer-the-mandalorian-emily-swallow |accessdate=January 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191205124950/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/11/the-armorer-the-mandalorian-emily-swallow |archive-date=December 5, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Crouse0102\">{{cite news |last=Crouse |first=Megan |title=Star Wars: 9 Unanswered Questions in The Mandalorian |work=[[Den of Geek]] |date=January 2, 2020 |url=https://www.denofgeek.com/us/tv/285142/star-wars-the-mandalorian-plot-holes-questions |accessdate=February 8, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103140516/https://www.denofgeek.com/us/tv/285142/star-wars-the-mandalorian-plot-holes-questions |archive-date=January 3, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Babu1203\">{{cite news |last=Babu |first=Armaan |title='The Mandalorian' star Emily Swallow talks about The Armorer and importance of keeping traditions of Mandalore alive |work=MEA Worldwide |date=December 2, 2019 |url=https://meaww.com/emily-swallow-interview-armorer-mandalorian-disney |accessdate=February 8, 2020}}</ref> including a new set of armor she makes for the Mandalorian.<ref name=\"Mitovich0128\" /><ref name=\"Snowden1122\">{{cite news |last=Snowden |first=Scott |title='The Mandalorian' Episode 3 Sees the Hunter Become the Hunted |work=[[Space.com]] |date=November 22, 2019 |url=https://www.space.com/star-wars-mandalorian-episode-3-review.html |accessdate=February 9, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191128121217/https://www.space.com/star-wars-mandalorian-episode-3-review.html |archive-date=November 28, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Babu1203\" /> In the first season finale \"Chapter 8: Redemption\", the Armorer instructs the Mandalorian to watch over and protect the Child,<ref name=\"Whalen1231\" /><ref name=\"Hough1230\">{{cite news |last=Hough |first=Q.V. |title=The Mandalorian: Who Plays The Armorer |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=December 30, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-armorer-actor-voice-emily-swallow/ |accessdate=February 8, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191231185519/https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-armorer-actor-voice-emily-swallow/ |archive-date=December 31, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Kain1227\">{{cite news |last=Kain |first=Erik |title=Star Wars 'The Mandalorian' Episode 8 Recap And Review: A Terrific Season Finale |work=[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2019/12/27/star-wars-the-mandalorian-episode-8-recap-and-review-a-terrific-season-finale/#3dd4bc9946b5 |accessdate=January 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191229033605/https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2019/12/27/star-wars-the-mandalorian-episode-8-recap-and-review-a-terrific-season-finale/#3dd4bc9946b5 |archive-date=December 29, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> and to reunite the Child with others of his own kind.<ref name=\"Keane1227\" /><ref name=\"Edwards0204\" /><ref name=\"Whalen1231\" /> The character was partially inspired by the films of Akira Kurosawa, as well as the history and culture of the samurai, particularly in the character's deliberately-paced movement and aura of authority.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ridgely |first=Charlie |title=Star Wars: The Mandalorian Star Emily Swallow Calls Season 2 \"Unexpected\" |work=Comicbook.com |date=January 24, 2020 |url=https://comicbook.com/starwars/2020/01/24/star-wars-mandalorian-season-2-unexpected-disney-plus-emily-swallow/ |accessdate=February 8, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125135815/https://comicbook.com/starwars/2020/01/24/star-wars-mandalorian-season-2-unexpected-disney-plus-emily-swallow/ |archive-date=January 25, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe Armorer is portrayed by [[Emily Swallow]], who provides both the character's voice and live-action performance,<ref name=\"Ridgely0122\">{{cite news |last=Ridgely |first=Charlie |title=Star Wars: The Mandalorian's Emily Swallow on Bringing The Armorer to Life |work=Comicbook.com |date=January 22, 2020 |url=https://comicbook.com/starwars/2020/01/22/star-wars-the-mandalorian-armorer-process-emily-swallow/ |accessdate=February 8, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126184845/https://comicbook.com/starwars/2020/01/22/star-wars-the-mandalorian-armorer-process-emily-swallow/ |archive-date=January 26, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"DelaCruz0123\">{{cite news |last=Dela Cruz |first=Judith Anne |title=Emily Swallow Says She Did All of The Armorer's Scenes in The Mandalorian Except One |work=Epicstream |date=January 23, 2020 |url=https://epicstream.com/news/JudithAnneDelaCruz/Emily-Swallow-Says-She-Did-All-Her-Scenes-in-The-Mandalorian-Except-One |accessdate=February 8, 2020}}</ref> while her stunts are performed by Lauren Mary Kim.<ref name=\"Ridgely0122\" /><ref name=\"Ridgely1230\" /> When Swallow auditioned for the role, she knew little about the character and did not know it was for a Star Wars series.<ref name=\"Breznican1122-a\" /> Aspects of ''The Mandalorian'' director [[Deborah Chow]]'s personality influenced Swallow's portrayal of the character.<ref name=\"Breznican1122-a\" /><ref name=\"Crouse0102\" /><ref name=\"Babu1203\" /> Kim's combat style in the Armorer's fight scenes was inspired by the Filipino [[Martial arts|martial art]] known as [[Arnis|Kali]].<ref name=\"Ridgely0122\" /><ref name=\"DelaCruz0123\" /> The Armorer has been received positively by fans and reviewers alike, and has been described as a fan favorite.<ref>{{cite news |title=\"The Mandalorian\" Actress Talks About Playing the Armorer |work=[[News 13]] |date=January 16, 2020 |url=https://www.mynews13.com/fl/orlando/entertainment/2020/01/16/-the-mandalorian--actress-talks-about-playing-the-armorer |accessdate=February 8, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200117212619/https://www.mynews13.com/fl/orlando/entertainment/2020/01/16/-the-mandalorian--actress-talks-about-playing-the-armorer |archive-date=January 17, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Jirak |first=Jamie |title=Star Wars: The Mandaloiran\u2019s Emily Swallow Shares Epic Fan Art of the Armorer |work=Comicbook.com |date=December 30, 2019 |url=https://comicbook.com/starwars/2019/12/29/star-wars-the-mandaloiran-emily-swallow-shares-epic-fan-art-the-armorer/ |accessdate=February 8, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230122931/https://comicbook.com/starwars/2019/12/29/star-wars-the-mandaloiran-emily-swallow-shares-epic-fan-art-the-armorer/ |archive-date=December 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media |author-last=Jordan |author-first=Alana |date=January 14, 2020 |title='The Mandalorian': Emily Swallow AKA The Armorer Wanted To Snuggle Baby Yoda! |work=MEA Worldwide |medium=[[YouTube]] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XhF4wSSNM_Y |access-date=February 9, 2020 |time=1:19\u20131:35 |quote=Your character in particular has just become such a fan favorite, but I will say there are so many people on the Internet that are begging, begging to see more of the Armorer in season two.}}</ref>\n\n===Kuiil===\n{{Main|Kuiil}}\n[[Image:NickNolte(cannesPhotocall).jpg|thumb|upright|alt=A man with white hair, wearing a tan jacket and two pairs of glasses on strings around his neck, looks off-camera.|Nick Nolte provided the voice of Kuiil, recording all the character's dialogue in one afternoon.]]\nKuiil is an alien of the [[List of Star Wars species (U\u2013Z)#Ugnaught|Ugnaught]] species, and a former indentured servant of the Galactic Empire.<ref name=\"Holman0102\">{{cite news |last=Holman |first=Leo |title=The Mandalorian: Kuiil Was the Series' Best Character \u2013 Here's Why |work=[[Comic Book Resources]] |date=January 2, 2020 |url=https://www.cbr.com/the-mandalorian-kuiil-series-best-character/ |accessdate=January 21, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103140349/https://www.cbr.com/the-mandalorian-kuiil-series-best-character/ |archive-date=January 3, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Hough0105\">{{cite news |last=Hough |first=Q.V. |title=The Mandalorian: Who Plays Kuiil |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=January 5, 2020 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-kuiil-actor-nick-nolte/ |accessdate=January 21, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200111025136/https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-kuiil-actor-nick-nolte/ |archive-date=January 11, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> He is living in solitude on the planet [[List of Star Wars planets and moons#Arvala-7|Arvala-7]] when he encounters the Mandalorian, who comes to the planet to find and capture the Child.<ref name=\"Holman0102\" /><ref name=\"Hough0105\" /> Kuiil assists him, and then later helps him rebuild his ship when it is dismantled by [[List of Star Wars species (F\u2013J)#Jawa|Jawas]].<ref name=\"Caicoya1228\">{{cite news |last=Caicoya |first=Ben |title=The Mandalorian Suffers Heartbreaking Losses in the Season 1 Finale |work=[[Comic Book Resources]] |date=December 28, 2019 |url=https://www.cbr.com/the-mandalorian-season-1-finale-deaths/ |accessdate=January 21, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191229140722/https://www.cbr.com/the-mandalorian-season-1-finale-deaths/ |archive-date=December 29, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Snowden1115\">{{cite news |last=Snowden |first=Scott |title='The Mandalorian' Episode 2 Is Fun, But Falls a Little Short |work=[[Space.com]] |date=November 15, 2019 |url=https://www.space.com/star-wars-mandalorian-episode-2-review.html |accessdate=January 24, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191115234800/https://www.space.com/star-wars-mandalorian-episode-2-review.html |archive-date=November 15, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Kuiil also rebuilds the bounty hunter droid IG-11 after the Mandalorian destroys him.<ref name=\"Pham1231\" /><ref name=\"Caicoya1228\" /><ref name=\"Kain1218\">{{cite news |last=Kain |first=Erik |title=Star Wars 'The Mandalorian' Episode 7 Recap And Review: 'The Reckoning' Is The Best Episode Yet |work=[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]] |date=December 18, 2019 |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2019/12/18/star-wars-the-mandalorian-episode-7-recap-and-review-the-best-episode-yet/#abd12ef70788 |accessdate=January 23, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222175408/https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2019/12/18/star-wars-the-mandalorian-episode-7-recap-and-review-the-best-episode-yet/#abd12ef70788 |archive-date=December 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Kuiil and IG-11 later join the Mandalorian on a mission to protect the Child from the Imperial remnant on the planet Nevarro,<ref name=\"Kain1218\" /><ref name=\"Howell1228\" /><ref name=\"Bundel1218\" /> where Kuiil is shot and killed by [[Stormtrooper (Star Wars)|Imperial Scout Troopers]] while attempting to bring the Child to safety.<ref name=\"Holman0102\" /><ref name=\"Kain1218\" /><ref name=\"Howell1228\" />\n\nKuiil is voiced by [[Nick Nolte]],<ref name=\"Holman0102\" /><ref name=\"Hough0105\" /> who completed his recordings for all the character's dialogue in a single afternoon.<ref name=\"Blend1220\">{{cite news |title=Star Wars May Have Given Nick Nolte A Very Surprising Character In The Mandalorian |work=CinemaBlend |date=December 20, 2018 |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/television/2463911/star-wars-may-have-given-nick-nolte-a-very-surprising-character-in-the-mandalorian |accessdate=January 23, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181223030723/https://www.cinemablend.com/television/2463911/star-wars-may-have-given-nick-nolte-a-very-surprising-character-in-the-mandalorian |archive-date=December 23, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Kuiil's motion capture performance was done by Misty Rosas,<ref name=\"Ridgely1230\">{{cite news |last=Ridgely |first=Charlie |title=Star Wars: The Mandolorian Fans Are Giving it Up for the Real Heroes of the Show |work=Comicbook.com |date=December 30, 2019 |url=https://comicbook.com/starwars/2019/12/30/star-wars-the-mandalorian-real-heroes-stunt-doubles/ |accessdate=January 23, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191231155423/https://comicbook.com/starwars/2019/12/30/star-wars-the-mandalorian-real-heroes-stunt-doubles/ |archive-date=December 31, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Kain1218\" /><ref name=\"Rosas5124\">{{cite podcast |last=Rosas |first=Misty |url=https://soundcloud.com/theinterestingpodcast/ep-108-misty-rosas |publisher=The Interesting Podcast |title=Ep. 108 Misty Rosas |date=January 21, 2020 |access-date=January 22, 2020 |time=51:24\u201352:02 |quote=\"The weight of it, because you didn't see it, I think, all the time, but the backpack I wore, that was filled form top to bottom with all of the animatronics. And they had wires right behind my neck so they would definitely, they would spread them out for me so I would have a little bit of motion. And then on each side, those pockets, which were pretty big, those were batteries. So the weight of him rode on my shoulders. So it was again a lot of core strength, so just pull the belly in.\"}}</ref> who during filming wore a face mask brought to life through animatronics and puppetry,<ref name=\"Blend1220\" /><ref name=\"Rosas5124\" /> with its electronics and wires concealed in the backpack and pockets of Kuiil's costume.<ref name=\"Rosas5124\" /> Kuiil has been received positively by reviewers and fans alike.<ref name=\"Pantoja0102\" /><ref name=\"Gatollari1113\">{{cite news |last=Gatollari |first=Mustafa |title=Nick Nolte Plays Kuiil in 'The Mandalorian' and He's One of the Best Parts of the Show |work=Distractify |date=November 13, 2019 |url=https://www.distractify.com/p/who-is-kuiil-the-mandalorian |accessdate=January 23, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191114161643/https://www.distractify.com/p/who-is-kuiil-the-mandalorian |archive-date=November 14, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Prudom0115\">{{cite news |last=Prudom |first=Laura |title=The Mandalorian Episode 8 Review |work=[[IGN]] |date=January 15, 2020 |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/12/27/the-mandalorian-episode-8-review-season-1-finale |accessdate=January 24, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191231092350/https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/12/27/the-mandalorian-episode-8-review-season-1-finale |archive-date=December 31, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Several critics have called him the best character on the show,<ref name=\"Holman0102\" /><ref name=\"Snowden1115\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Plante |first=Corey |title=Nick Nolte's 'Mandalorian' character isn't a jerk -- he's brilliant. I have spoken. |work=[[Inverse (website)|Inverse]] |date=November 18, 2019 |url=https://www.inverse.com/article/61012-the-mandalorian-nick-nolte-s-kuill-is-better-than-baby-yoda |accessdate=January 23, 2020}}</ref> and his signature line \"I have spoken\" became one of the better-known and best-liked lines of dialogue from the series.<ref name=\"Pantoja0102\" /><ref name=\"Gatollari1113\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Evans |first=Kiki |title=The Mandalorian Characters Sorted Into Their Hogwarts Houses |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=January 23, 2020 |url=https://screenrant.com/harry-potter-star-wars-mandalorian-characters-sorted-hogwarts-houses/ |accessdate=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===IG-11===\n{{Main|IG-11}}\n[[Image:Taika Waititi by Gage Skidmore 2.jpg|thumb|upright|alt=A man with black and silver slicked-back hair wears a purple patterned shirt and holds a microphone.|IG-11 was voiced by Taika Waititi, who also directed an episode of ''The Mandalorian''.]]\nIG-11 is a bounty hunter droid who initially attempts to capture and kill the Child,<ref name=\"Kirby1112\">{{cite news |last=Kirby |first=Meaghan |title=''The Mandalorian'' series premiere recap: The Mandalorian embarks on a dangerous assignment |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=November 12, 2019 |url=https://ew.com/recap/the-mandalorian-series-premiere/ |accessdate=January 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211031145/https://ew.com/recap/the-mandalorian-series-premiere/ |archive-date=December 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Carbone0113\">{{cite news |last=Carbone |first=Gina |title=The Mandalorian's Taika Waititi Calls His IG-11 'The Hero Of The Entire Season' |work=CinemaBlend |date=January 13, 2020 |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/television/2488421/the-mandalorian-taika-waititi-calls-his-character-ig-11-the-hero-of-the-entire-season |accessdate=January 14, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200114023214/https://www.cinemablend.com/television/2488421/the-mandalorian-taika-waititi-calls-his-character-ig-11-the-hero-of-the-entire-season |archive-date=January 14, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Hough0102\">{{cite news |last=Hough |first=Q.V. |title=The Mandalorian: Who Plays IG-11 |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=January 2, 2020 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-ig11-actor-voice-taika-waititi/ |accessdate=January 14, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103135412/https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-ig11-actor-voice-taika-waititi/ |archive-date=January 3, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> but is later reprogrammed to become its [[Nursing|nurse]] and protector.<ref name=\"Carbone0113\" /><ref name=\"Ridgely1227\">{{cite news |last=Ridgely |first=Charlie |title=IG-11 Is Now Many Star Wars Fans' Favorite Droid After The Mandalorian Finale |work=Comicbook.com |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://comicbook.com/starwars/2019/12/27/star-wars-the-mandalorian-ig-11-fan-reactions/ |accessdate=January 14, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191228125819/https://comicbook.com/starwars/2019/12/27/star-wars-the-mandalorian-ig-11-fan-reactions/ |archive-date=December 28, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The Mandalorian first encounters IG-11 when both attempt to collect the bounty on the Child. They work together to extract the Child from a gang of mercenaries,<ref name=\"Kirby1112\" /><ref name=\"Hough0102\" /><ref name=\"Komonibo1115\">{{cite news |last=Komonibo |first=Ineye |title=What's Up With The Mandalorian's Bounty Hunting Droid & That Big Episode 1 Twist? |work=[[Refinery29]] |date=November 15, 2019 |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/11/8741465/mandalorian-bounty-hunter-droid-ig-11-voice-actor-episodes |accessdate=January 15, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116174825/https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/11/8741465/mandalorian-bounty-hunter-droid-ig-11-voice-actor-episodes |archive-date=November 16, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> but when IG-11 tries to kill the Child, the Mandalorian instead shoots and kills the droid.<ref name=\"Kirby1112\" /><ref name=\"Hough0102\" /><ref name=\"Hussain0114\">{{cite news |last=Hussain |first=Humza |title=The Mandalorian: Taika Waititi Wants Fans To Petition To Bring Back IG-11 |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=January 14, 2020 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-season-2-ig11-return-petition-taika-waititi/ |accessdate=January 14, 2020}}</ref> IG-11's remains are recovered by [[Kuiil]], who repairs and reprograms him.<ref>{{cite news |last=Thorne |first=Will |title='The Mandalorian': 5 Burning Questions From 'The Reckoning' |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=December 18, 2019 |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/mandalorian-episode-7-questions-baby-yoda-1203446445/ |accessdate=January 15, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200102115528/https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/mandalorian-episode-7-questions-baby-yoda-1203446445/ |archive-date=January 2, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The droid later join the Mandalorian on a mission to Nevarro to protect the Child from the Imperial remnant,<ref>{{cite news |last=Kane |first=Alex |title=The Mandalorian recap: Chapter 7 'The Reckoning' |work=[[USA Today]] |date=December 18, 2019 |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/reviewedcom/2019/12/18/mandalorian-recap-chapter-7-the-reckoning-disney-plus/2686077001/ |accessdate=January 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200114203021/https://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/reviewedcom/2019/12/18/mandalorian-recap-chapter-7-the-reckoning-disney-plus/2686077001/ |archive-date=January 14, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> and though the Mandalorian does not initially trust him,<ref name=\"Bundel1218\">{{cite news |last=Bundel |first=Ani |title=Is Kuiil Really Dead On 'The Mandalorian'? Things Don't Look Good |work=[[Elite Daily]] |date=December 18, 2019 |url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/is-kuiil-really-dead-on-the-mandalorian-things-dont-look-good-19494702 |accessdate=January 23, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219143603/https://www.elitedaily.com/p/is-kuiil-really-dead-on-the-mandalorian-things-dont-look-good-19494702 |archive-date=December 19, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> IG-11 ultimately sacrifices his own life to protect the Child and his allies.<ref name=\"Carbone0113\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Dumaraog |first=Ana |title=The Mandalorian Season 1's Ending Explained (In Detail) |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-season-1-ending-explained-darksaber-future/ |accessdate=January 14, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191228131503/https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-season-1-ending-explained-darksaber-future/ |archive-date=December 28, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Outlaw |first=Kofi |title=Star Wars: The Mandalorian Meme Puts IG-11 on the High Ground Over Anakin Skywalker |work=Comicbook.com |date=January 6, 2020 |url=https://comicbook.com/starwars/2020/01/06/star-wars-mandalorian-ig-11-anakin-skywalker-revenge-sith-high-ground-memes/ |accessdate=January 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200106215922/https://comicbook.com/starwars/2020/01/06/star-wars-mandalorian-ig-11-anakin-skywalker-revenge-sith-high-ground-memes/ |archive-date=January 6, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIG-11 is voiced by [[Taika Waititi]],<ref name=\"Hough0102\" /><ref name=\"Hussain0114\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Hood |first=Cooper |title=The Mandalorian Season 1 Finale Cast Guide: Returning Characters & Cameos |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-season-1-finale-cast-character-cameo-guide/ |accessdate=January 14, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191228131744/https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-season-1-finale-cast-character-cameo-guide/ |archive-date=December 28, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> who was offered the part by Jon Favreau based on their work together on [[Marvel Cinematic Universe|Marvel]] films.<ref name=\"Radish1030\" /><ref name=\"Komonibo1115\" /> Waititi said he tried to create a voice that lacked human emotion while still maintaining some semblance of humanity,<ref>{{cite AV media |people=[[Taika Waititi|Waititi, Taika]] |date=August 23, 2019 |title=The Mandalorian: Taika Waititi on Finding the Voice of IG-11 - D23 2019 |medium=[[YouTube]] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kVxXE0qN38I |access-date=January 14, 2020 |time=0:11\u20130:26 |publisher=[[IGN]] |quote=It was actually really hard. It was really hard, guys, to find that robot voice. Because you've got to take away personality and emotion, but it can't be completely devoid, so it's really a subtle little thing there. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825063603/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kVxXE0qN38I |archive-date=August 25, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> describing it as a cross between [[Siri]] and [[HAL 9000]].<ref name=\"Gallagher1111\">{{cite news |last=Gallagher |first=Caitlin |title=IG-11 From 'The Mandalorian' Is A New, Bounty Hunting Droid In The Expanded Universe |work=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]] |date=November 11, 2019 |url=https://www.bustle.com/p/ig-11-from-the-mandalorian-is-a-new-bounty-hunting-droid-in-the-expanded-universe-19310297 |accessdate=January 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191228074014/https://www.bustle.com/p/ig-11-from-the-mandalorian-is-a-new-bounty-hunting-droid-in-the-expanded-universe-19310297 |archive-date=December 28, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Hibberd |first=James |title=''The Mandalorian'' unmasked: 'We did things no ''Star Wars'' fan has ever seen' |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=September 5, 2019 |url=https://ew.com/tv/2019/09/05/inside-the-mandalorian-star-wars/ |accessdate=January 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905185539/https://ew.com/tv/2019/09/05/inside-the-mandalorian-star-wars/ |archive-date=September 5, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> IG-11 was mistaken for the ''Star Wars'' bounty hunter [[List of Star Wars characters#IG-88|IG-88]] when first unveiled due to the resemblance between the two characters.<ref name=\"Gallagher1111\" /><ref name=\"Breznican0414\" /> IG-11 has been received positively by reviewers and fans alike,<ref name=\"Carbone0113\" /><ref name=\"Ridgely1227\" /> with some calling him one of the best droids in the franchise.<ref name=\"Ridgely1227\" />\n\n===Cara Dune===\n{{Main|Cara Dune}}\n[[Image:Gina Carano by Gage Skidmore.jpg|thumb|upright|alt=A woman with dark brown hair wearing a leather jacket sits in front of a microphone and smiles at something off-camera.|Former mixed martial artist Gina Carano portrayed Cara Dune.]]\nCara \"Carasynthia\" Dune is a former [[Rebel Alliance|Rebel]] shock trooper who became a [[mercenary]] after the fall of the Empire.<ref name=\"Pham1231\">{{cite news |last=Pham |first=Danny |title=The Mandalorian: 10 Most Interesting Characters In Season 1 |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=December 31, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/the-mandalorian-disney-characters-best-most-interesting-season-one/ |accessdate=January 20, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200101130131/https://screenrant.com/the-mandalorian-disney-characters-best-most-interesting-season-one/ |archive-date=January 1, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Gramuglia0414\">{{cite news |last=Gramuglia |first=Anthony |title=Star Wars: The Mandalorian: Gina Carano Explains Her Character |work=[[Comic Book Resources]] |date=April 14, 2019 |url=https://www.cbr.com/mandalorian-gina-carano-character/ |accessdate=January 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420042731/https://www.cbr.com/mandalorian-gina-carano-character/ |archive-date=April 20, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Originally from [[Alderaan]],<ref name=\"Plante1227\">{{cite news |last=Plante |first=Corey |title='The Mandalorian' finale Easter egg explains why Cara Dune hates the Empire |work=[[Inverse (website)|Inverse]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://www.inverse.com/article/62020-mandalorian-spoilers-episode-8-finale-easter-egg-cara-dune-alderaan |accessdate=January 18, 2020}}</ref>  Cara is a highly trained warrior and skilled battle tactician.<ref>{{cite news |last=Elvy |first=Craig |title=The Mandalorian: Every Star Wars Easter Egg In Episode 4 |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-show-episode-4-star-wars-easter-eggs/ |accessdate=January 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223052755/https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-show-episode-4-star-wars-easter-eggs/ |archive-date=December 23, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=The Mandalorian Is the Only Smart Soldier in the Star Wars Galaxy |work=[[Wired (magazine)|Wired]] |date=January 14, 2020 |url=https://www.wired.com/story/mandalorian-star-wars-soldier-tactics/ |accessdate=January 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200115192603/https://www.wired.com/story/mandalorian-star-wars-soldier-tactics/ |archive-date=January 15, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> She harbors an intense hatred for the Galactic Empire,<ref name=\"Plante1227\" /> and is having trouble readjusting to post-war life.<ref name=\"Baver0118\">{{cite news |last=Baver |first=Kristin |title=SWCC 2019: 9 Things We Learned from ''The Mandalorian'' Panel |work=[[Star Wars|StarWars.com]] |date=April 14, 2019 |url=https://www.starwars.com/news/swcc-2019-9-things-we-learned-from-the-mandalorian-panel |accessdate=January 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415024016/https://www.starwars.com/news/swcc-2019-9-things-we-learned-from-the-mandalorian-panel |archive-date=April 15, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Gramuglia0414\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Baver |first=Kristin |title=Everything We Know About ''The Mandalorian'' So Far |work=[[Star Wars|StarWars.com]] |date=November 8, 2019 |url=https://www.starwars.com/news/everything-we-know-about-the-mandalorian |accessdate=January 19, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218101204/https://www.starwars.com/news/everything-we-know-about-the-mandalorian |archive-date=December 18, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Cara first encounters the Mandalorian on the planet [[List of Star Wars planets and moons#Sorgan|Sorgan]], where they work together to protect a local village from raiders.<ref name=\"Robinson1129\">{{cite news |last=Robinson |first=Joanna |title=Why ''The Mandalorian'' Star Gina Carano Thought She Was Playing a Wookiee |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/11/the-mandalorian-gina-carano-cara-dune-costume-still-watching-interview |accessdate=January 17, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191201230539/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/11/the-mandalorian-gina-carano-cara-dune-costume-still-watching-interview |archive-date=December 1, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> He later recruits her to help protect the Child from the Imperial remnant.<ref>{{cite news |last=Breznican |first=Anthony |title=Baby Yoda is Going to Hurt Someone |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |date=December 18, 2019 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/12/the-mandalorian-chapter-7-recap |accessdate=January 17, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"White1218\">{{cite news |last=White |first=Brett |title='The Mandalorian' on Disney+: 5 Things You May Have Missed in Chapter 7 |work=[[New York Post|Decider.com]] |date=December 18, 2020 |url=https://decider.com/2019/12/18/the-mandalorian-chapter-7-easter-eggs/ |accessdate=January 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200110064117/https://decider.com/2019/12/18/the-mandalorian-chapter-7-easter-eggs/ |archive-date=January 10, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Hall |first=Charlie |title=Mandalorian is making sense of the time between Return of Jedi and Force Awakens |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |date=December 18, 2019 |url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/12/18/21026895/mandalorian-episode-7-recap-timeline-return-of-jedi-force-awakens |accessdate=January 19, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219150605/https://www.polygon.com/2019/12/18/21026895/mandalorian-episode-7-recap-timeline-return-of-jedi-force-awakens |archive-date=December 19, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nCara is portrayed by former [[Mixed martial arts|mixed martial artist]] [[Gina Carano]], for whom Favreau specifically created the character, without auditioning any other actresses.<ref name=\"Robinson1129\" /><ref name=\"Davids1203\">{{cite news |last=Davids |first=Brian |title='The Mandalorian' Star Gina Carano on Cara Dune's Secret Backstory |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=December 3, 2019 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/mandalorian-gina-carano-cara-dunes-secret-history-1259402 |accessdate=January 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191204175839/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/mandalorian-gina-carano-cara-dunes-secret-history-1259402 |archive-date=December 4, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Hedash |first=Kara |title=The Mandalorian: Cara Dune Backstory (& Possible Future) Explained |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=December 1, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/star-wars-mandalorian-cara-dune-backstory-rebellion-show-future-explained/ |accessdate=January 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191202144956/https://screenrant.com/star-wars-mandalorian-cara-dune-backstory-rebellion-show-future-explained/ |archive-date=December 2, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Favreau sought to create a powerful and independent character, but one different from [[Princess Leia]] or other strong ''Star Wars'' female characters.<ref name=\"Davids1203\" /> Carano performed many of her own stunts,<ref name=\"Baver0118\" /><ref name=\"Rorke1111\">{{cite news |last=Rorke |first=Robert |title=Which actors from Disney+'s 'The Mandalorian' did their own stunts? |work=[[New York Post]] |date=November 11, 2019 |url=https://nypost.com/2019/11/11/which-actors-from-disneys-the-mandalorian-did-their-own-stunts/ |accessdate=January 20, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200105095323/https://nypost.com/2019/11/11/which-actors-from-disneys-the-mandalorian-did-their-own-stunts/ |archive-date=January 5, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> and she credits [[Bryce Dallas Howard]], who directed the character's first appearance in \"[[Chapter 4: Sanctuary]]\", with helping translate the character from the script to the screen.<ref name=\"Robinson1129\" /> Cara has been received positively by reviewers and fans,<ref name=\"Davids1203\" /> and has been described as a feminist role model, with some critics calling her unique even among the ''Star Wars'' franchise's female characters due to her physicality and combat skills.<ref>{{cite news |last=Luchini |first=Olivia |title=The Mandalorian's Cara Dune Is the Feminist Badass We Needed From Star Wars |work=[[PopSugar]] |date=December 14, 2019 |url=https://www.popsugar.com/entertainment/why-cara-dune-is-feminist-star-wars-icon-46978992 |accessdate=January 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191214132733/https://www.popsugar.com/entertainment/why-cara-dune-is-feminist-star-wars-icon-46978992 |archive-date=December 14, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Moff Gideon===\n{{Main|Moff Gideon}}\n[[Image:Giancarlo Esposito SXSW 2017 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|alt=A smiling man with great and black hair and facial ahir, wearing a black buttoned shirt and patterned black blazer, looks directly into the camera.|Giancarlo Esposito, who had previously worked with Jon Favreau on several projects, portrayed Moff Gideon.]]\nMoff Gideon is the leader of the Imperial remnant and the primary antagonist of ''The Mandalorian''.<ref>{{cite news |last=Dumaraog |first=Ana |title=The Mandalorian Season 2 Will Answer BIG Star Wars Questions |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=December 31, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-season-2-star-wars-questions-baby-yoda-darksaber/ |accessdate=January 25, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Romano |first=Evan |title=''The Mandalorian''{{'}}s Primary Villain, Moff Gideon, Has A Face TV Fans Already Fear |work=[[Men's Health]] |date=December 18, 2019 |url=https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/a30267279/the-mandalorian-moff-gideon-giancarlo-esposito/ |accessdate=January 25, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Trivedi |first=Sachin |title='The Mandalorian' Season 2: What To Expect From New Villain Moff Gideon |work=[[International Business Times]] |date=January 23, 2020 |url=https://www.ibtimes.com/mandalorian-season-2-what-expect-new-villain-moff-gideon-2907831 |accessdate=January 26, 2020}}</ref> Few details of his backstory have yet been revealed. He was previously an operative in the Imperial Security Bureau, a covert intelligence arm and secret police for the Empire,<ref name=\"Prudom0115\" /><ref name=\"Saavedra1227\">{{cite news |last=Saavedra |first=John |title=Star Wars: The Mandalorian - Who Is Moff Gideon? |work=[[Den of Geek]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://www.denofgeek.com/us/tv/star-wars/285023/the-mandalorian-moff-gideon |accessdate=January 26, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Dumaraog |first=Ana |title=The Mandalorian Theory: Moff Gideon Wants To Become The New Darth Vader |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=January 4, 2020 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-moff-gideon-new-darth-vader-darksaber-force-theory/ |accessdate=January 25, 2020}}</ref> and played a role in past efforts to eliminate the Mandalorians.<ref name=\"Saavedra1227\" /><ref name=\"Melrose1227\">{{cite news |last=Melrose |first=Kevin |title=The Mandalorian Season 1's Surprising Final Scene, Explained |work=[[Comic Book Resources]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://www.cbr.com/the-mandalorian-season-1-finale-darksaber-moff-gideon/ |accessdate=January 25, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Hurley |first=Laura |title=What The Mandalorian's Big Finale Reveal Could Mean For Season 2, The Clone Wars And More |work=CinemaBlend |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/television/2487464/what-the-mandalorians-big-finale-reveal-could-mean-for-season-2-the-clone-wars-revival-and-more |accessdate=January 25, 2020}}</ref> In ''The Mandalorian'', Moff Gideon is attempting to abduct the Child for undisclosed reasons,<ref name=\"Prudom0115\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Jackson |first=Matthew |title=Giancarlo Esposito teases Moff Gideon's dark plans for Baby Yoda in The Mandalorian |work=[[SyFy]] |date=January 24, 2020 |url=https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/giancarlo-esposito-moff-gideon-baby-yoda-the-mandalorian |accessdate=January 25, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Lash0117\">{{cite news |last=Lash |first=Jolie |title=The Mandalorian Season 2: Giancarlo Esposito Offers Clue on Why Moff Gideon Wants Baby Yoda |work=[[IGN]] |date=January 17, 2020 |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/the-mandalorian-season-2-moff-gideon-baby-yoda-darksaber |accessdate=January 24, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200121054150/https://www.ign.com/articles/the-mandalorian-season-2-moff-gideon-baby-yoda-darksaber |archive-date=January 21, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> and he briefly traps the Mandalorian and his allies on Nevarro in an unsuccessful attempt to obtain the Child.<ref name=\"Silliman1218\" /><ref name=\"Melrose1227\" /><ref name=\"Roman1227\">{{cite news |last=Roman |first=Julian |title=The Mandalorian Season 1 Finale Recap and Review: The Phoenix Rises |work=TVweb |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://tvweb.com/the-mandalorian-season-1-episode-eight-recap-review/ |accessdate=January 25, 2020}}</ref> Gideon reveals he knows secret details about the Mandalorian and his allies,<ref name=\"Keane1227\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Kirby |first=Meaghan |title=''The Mandalorian'' season finale recap: Mando and Moff Gideon face off |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://ew.com/recap/the-mandalorian-season-1-finale/ |accessdate=January 26, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Snowden1227\">{{cite news |last=Snowden |first=Scott |title='The Mandalorian' Finale is an Electrifying End to Season 1 |work=[[Space.com]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://www.space.com/star-wars-the-mandalorian-episode-8-review.html |accessdate=January 20, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112033204/https://www.space.com/star-wars-the-mandalorian-episode-8-review.html |archive-date=January 12, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> and is the first character in the series to reveal the Mandalorian's real name, Din Djarin.<ref name=\"Lash0117\" /><ref name=\"Roman1227\" /><ref name=\"Snowden1227\" /> In the final scene of the first season finale \"[[Chapter 8: Redemption]], it is revealed that Gideon possesses the [[Darksaber (fictional weapon)|Darksaber]], a Mandalorian lightsaber.<ref name=\"Lash0117\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Knox |first=Kelly |title=What is the Darksaber? |work=[[Star Wars|StarWars.com]] |publisher=[[Lucasfilm]] |date=February 11, 2020 |url=https://www.starwars.com/news/what-is-the-darksaber |accessdate=February 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221195525/https://www.starwars.com/news/what-is-the-darksaber |archive-date=February 21, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nGideon is portrayed by [[Giancarlo Esposito]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Romano |first=Evan |title=Everything We Know About ''The Mandalorian'' Cast and Characters |work=[[Men's Health]] |date=November 5, 2019 |url=https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/g29697502/the-mandalorian-cast/ |accessdate=January 25, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Caulfield |first=AJ |title=The Mandalorian: First footage, new photos, character details revealed at Star Wars Celebration |work=[[Looper (website)|Looper]] |date=April 14, 2019 |url=https://www.looper.com/150249/the-mandalorian-first-footage-new-photos-character-details-revealed-at-star-wars-celebration/ |accessdate=January 25, 2020}}</ref> He was recruited for the part by Jon Favreau,<ref name=\"EspositoEW\">{{cite video |people=[[Giancarlo Esposito|Esposito, Giancarlo]] |title=''The Mandalorian'' recap: Mando makes a terrible mistake |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=November 22, 2019 |url=https://ew.com/recap/the-mandalorian-season-1-episode-3/ |accessdate=January 26, 2020 |time=2:20\u20132:57 |quote=I know for me, these films, they formed a part of my childhood and they gave me the ability to dream and to feel like they would take me to another place. And when you have a film that does that in an imaginary world that could be so real, it's very exciting for you. They taught me how to feel like a champion, how to feel like there are always going to be challenges but that if we are able to come together as a family somehow and if I can believe in myself, I can overcome anything. So for me to be a part of this was very exciting when Jon asked me. I worked with him before.}}</ref> who had previously worked with Esposito on several projects.<ref>{{cite video |people=[[Giancarlo Esposito|Esposito, Giancarlo]] |title=Giancarlo Esposito Opens Up About 'Exciting' Role in 'The Mandalorian' (Exclusive) |work=[[Entertainment Tonight]] |date=September 22, 2019 |url=https://www.etonline.com/giancarlo-esposito-opens-up-about-exciting-role-in-the-mandalorian-exclusive-132978 |accessdate=January 25, 2020 |time=1:38\u20132:29 |quote=I've worked with him three times. Once on the pilot of ''Revolution'', a show I did with Eric Kripke that was so wonderful. Made his acquaintance, and then he asked me to do a ''Destiny'' commercial where I was reaching Rudyard Kipling, and we started to talk about ''The Lion King'' and Disney movies that we really really loved, so he tapped me for ''Jungle Book'' and I was able to do that with him. He is very specific and wonderful because he's an actor. So you get an actor directing you, he knows what you're feeling inside, he knows where you're going, and he gives you suggestions you can really utilize and use. Not just about, 'Oh, here go, stand there we want to do a shot like this.' Explains the shot and says, What do you feel inside you?' That's a respectful, wonderful actor turned director turned writer turned producer. The incredible and fabulous Jon Favreau.}}</ref><ref name=\"EspositoCollider127\">{{cite video |people=[[Giancarlo Esposito|Esposito, Giancarlo]] |title='The Mandalorian' Actor Giancarlo Esposito Describes the New Technology Used on the 'Star Wars' Show |work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |date=April 18, 2019 |url=https://collider.com/the-mandalorian-filming-details-giancarlo-esposito/#george-lucas |accessdate=January 25, 2020 |time=1:27\u20131:50 |quote=Jon and I did ''Revolution''. We did ''Jungle Book'' together. We did a commercial for ''Destiny'' that led to ''Jungle Book'', and our conversation on ''Destiny'', then he asked me to do a ''Destiny'' commercial where I was reaching Rudyard, reading that wonderful poem, Mowgli, the ''Jungle Book'' story, and Jon said wouldn't it be great if that was redone? And I said, 'Man, that would be really fantastic.' A year later, he's calling me to do that.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Graser |first=Marc |title=First Look: Jon Favreau Directs Live Action Promo for Videogame 'Destiny' |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=May 23, 2013 |url=https://variety.com/2013/digital/games/first-look-the-live-action-trailer-for-bungies-destiny-exclusive-1200486874/ |accessdate=January 25, 2020}}</ref> Gideon has been received positively by reviewers and fans.<ref name=\"Keane1227\" /><ref name=\"Snowden1218\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Dwilson |first=Stephanie Dube |title=Moff Gideon on 'The Mandalorian': Background, Theories & Predictions |work=[[Heavy.com]] |date=December 18, 2019 |url=https://heavy.com/entertainment/2019/12/moff-gideon-the-mandalorian/ |accessdate=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Guest characters==\nThe following is a supplementary list of guest stars that appear in lesser roles or make significant [[cameo appearances]].\n<!-- NOTE: Characters included in this section have appeared in only one episode. -->\n\n===Mythrol===\nAn alien of the species Mythrol appears in the opening scenes of the series premiere \"Chapter 1: The Mandalorian\", in which the Mandalorian captures him to collect a bounty on him.<ref name=\"Thomas1230\" /><ref name=\"Schedeen1227\" /><ref name=\"Snowden1113\">{{cite news |last=Snowden |first=Scott |title='The Mandalorian' Episode 1 Perfects the Small-Screen 'Sci-Fi Western' |work=[[Space.com]] |date=November 13, 2019 |url=https://www.space.com/star-wars-the-mandalorian-episode-1-review.html |accessdate=February 17, 2020}}</ref> Blue-skinned and ambitious, with fins on his face,<ref name=\"Prahl1217\" /><ref name=\"Romain1115\" /> the Mythrol is ultimately delivered to the Bounty Hunters' Guild.<ref name=\"Kirby1112\" /><ref name=\"Snowden1113\" /> The Mythrol is portrayed by comedian [[Horatio Sanz]],<ref name=\"Thomas1230\" /><ref name=\"Schedeen1227\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Adams |first=Sam |title=Disney\u2019s Live-Action Star Wars Show Looks Great, but So Far It Isn\u2019t |work=[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]] |date=November 12, 2019 |url=https://slate.com/culture/2019/11/the-mandalorian-review-star-wars-series-disney-plus.html |accessdate=February 17, 2020}}</ref> a long-time fan of ''Star Wars''.<ref>{{cite news |last=Romano |first=Evan |title=Comedians Horatio Sanz and Brian Posehn Made Sneaky Cameos in the First Episode of ''The Mandalorian'' |work=[[Men's Health]] |date=November 13, 2019 |url=https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/a29786836/horatio-sanz-brian-posehn-the-mandalorian/ |accessdate=February 17, 2020}}</ref> His make-up was done by make-up artist Brian Sipe.<ref>{{cite tweet |last=Sanz |first=Horatio |author-link=Horatio Sanz |user=MrHoratioSanz |number=1194829168027918337 |date=November 13, 2019 |title=@themandalorian @starwars @BrianSipemakeup @hookuptattoos}}</ref>\n\n===Paz Vizla===\n{{Main|Paz Vizla}}\nPaz Vizla is one of the warriors in the Mandalorian tribe on Nevarro. Strong and physically imposing,<ref name=\"Breznican1122-b\">{{cite news |last=Breznican |first=Anthony  |author-link=Anthony Breznican |title=''The Mandalorian Episode Three Easter Eggs: Life Day, Iron Man, Princess Leia, and More |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |date=November 22, 2019 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/11/the-mandalorian-episode-three-recap |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Kleinman0205\">{{cite news |last=Kleinman |first=Jake |title=The Mandalorian Season 2 could bring back this fan-favorite for a spinoff, Disney hints |work=[[Inverse (website)|Inverse]] |date=February 5, 2020 |url=https://www.inverse.com/entertainment/mandalorian-season-2-release-date-theory-spinoff-cast |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Anderton1125\">{{cite news |last=Anderton |first=Ethan |title=Awesome New 'The Mandalorian' Character That Isn't Baby Yoda Is Getting a 'Star Wars' Black Series Figure |work=[[/Film]] |date=November 25, 2019 |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/new-the-mandalorian-action-figure/ |accessdate=February 13, 2020}}</ref> he is a heavy infantry fighter.<ref name=\"Anderton1125\" /><ref name=\"Snowden1129\">{{cite news |last=Snowden |first=Scott |title= 'The Mandalorian' Episode 4 is a Nod to a Classic Western Movie Trope |work=[[Space.com]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://www.space.com/star-wars-the-mandalorian-episode-4-review.html |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref> He appears in the episode \"Chapter 3: The Sin\", where he initially quarrels with the Mandalorian for working with the Empire,<ref name=\"Snowden1122\" /><ref name=\"Girolamo0103\">{{cite news |last=Girolamo |first=Dan |title=The Mandalorian: Who Plays Paz Vizla (Under The Armor) |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=January 3, 2020 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-paz-vizla-actor-tait-fletcher/ |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Dumaraog1122\">{{cite news |last=Dumaraog |first=Ana |title=Jon Favreau's Mandalorian Episode 3 Cameo Confirmed |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=November 22, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/jon-favreau-star-wars-mandalorian-episode-3-cameo/ |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref> but later comes to his assistance when the Mandalorian is being attacked.<ref name=\"Snowden1122\" /><ref name=\"Girolamo0103\" /><ref name=\"Dumaraog1122\" /> Paz Vizla is voiced by Jon Favreau,<ref name=\"Schedeen1227\">{{cite news |last=Schedeen |first=Jesse |title=The Mandalorian Cast: Every Character and Cameo in Season 1 |work=[[IGN]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/12/27/the-mandalorian-cast-cameos-celebrity-who-was-in-episode |accessdate=February 13, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Dockterman |first=Eliana |title=Jason Sudeikis' Stormtrooper Punched Baby Yoda in The Mandalorian Finale and Fans Are Not Pleased |work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |date=December 28, 2019 |url=https://time.com/5756141/jason-sudeikis-the-mandalorian/ |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Gates |first=Christopher |title=Why Star Wars: The Clone Wars' final season will blow everyone away |work=[[ZergNet|Looper]] |date=January 29, 2020 |url=https://www.looper.com/185717/why-star-wars-the-clone-wars-final-season-will-blow-everyone-away/ |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref> who previously voiced a similarly-named Mandalorian warlord named Pre Vizsla on the series ''Star Wars: The Clone Wars''.<ref name=\"Breznican1122-b\" /><ref name=\"Kleinman0205\" /><ref name=\"Girolamo0103\" /> Stunt performer and former mixed martial artist Tait Fletcher was the live-action body double for Paz Vizla.<ref name=\"Thomas1230\">{{cite news |last=Thomas |first=Leah Marilla |title=A Guide To ''The Mandalorian''{{'}}s Cast Of Characters... So Far |work=[[Refinery29]] |date=December 30, 2019 |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/11/8819249/the-mandalorian-cast-characters-actors |accessdate=February 13, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Girolamo0103\" /><ref name=\"Dumaraog1122\" />\n\n===Omera===\nOmera is a krill farmer and widow living on a village on Sorgan with her daughter, Winta, in the episode \"Chapter 4: Sanctuary\".<ref name=\"Thomas1230\" /><ref name=\"Young1129\">{{cite news |last=Young |first=Bryan |title='The Mandalorian' Goes Full 'Seven Samurai' With \"Sanctuary\" |work=[[/Film]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/the-mandalorian-sanctuary-review/ |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Phillips |first=Patrick |title=Why Omera from The Mandalorian looks so familiar |work=[[ZergNet|Looper]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://www.looper.com/178014/why-omera-from-the-mandalorian-looks-so-familiar/ |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref> When the villagers hire the Mandalorian and Cara Dune to protect them from Klatooinian raiders, Omera befriends the Mandalorian, and the two appear attracted to each other.<ref name=\"MHRomano1213\" /><ref name=\"White1202\">{{cite news |last=White |first=Brett |title=Who Is Omera on 'The Mandalorian'? Meet Julia Jones |work=[[New York Post|Decider]] |date=December 2, 2019 |url=https://decider.com/2019/12/02/the-mandalorian-chapter-4-julia-jones/ |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Plante1129\">{{cite news |last=Plante |first=Corey |title='The Mandalorian' Episode 4 confirmed a bombshell about Mando's past |work=[[Inverse (website)|Inverse]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://www.inverse.com/article/61345-mandalorian-episode-4-spoilers-sanctuary-confirms-mando-past |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref> She participates in the village's successful defense of the village and elimination of the raiders.<ref name=\"Keane1130\">{{cite news |last=Keane |first=Sean |title=The Mandalorian episode 4 recap: Baby Yoda finds happiness |work=[[CNET]] |date=November 30, 2019 |url=https://www.cnet.com/news/the-mandalorian-episode-4-sanctuary-recap-baby-yoda-finds-happiness/ |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Babu |first=Armaan |title='The Mandalorian' answers fans' biggest question about his helmet and reveals a lot about his backstory in the process |work=MEA WorldWide |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://meaww.com/the-mandalorian-answers-fans-biggest-question-helmet-star-wars-disney-backstory |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Sepinwall |first=Alan |author-link=Alan Sepinwall |title='The Mandalorian' Recap: Hang Onto Your Hat |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/tv/tv-recaps/mandalorian-recap-episode-4-sanctuary-919655/ |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref> Omera is portrayed by [[Julia Jones]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Marc |first=Christopher |title='Westworld' Actress Julia Jones Plays A Character Named Omera In 'The Mandalorian' |work=HN Entertainment |date=September 6, 2019 |url=https://hnentertainment.co/westworld-actress-julia-jones-plays-a-character-named-omera-in-the-mandalorian/ |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Carbone |first=Gina |title=The Mandalorian's Boom Mic Mistake In Episode 4 Gets Compared To Game Of Thrones' Coffee Cup |work=CinemaBlend |date=December 2, 2019 |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/television/2485836/the-mandalorians-boom-mic-mistake-in-episode-4-gets-compared-to-game-of-thrones-coffee-cup |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Thorne |first=Will |title='The Mandalorian': 5 Burning Questions From Episode 5 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/mandalorian-episode-5-questions-baby-yoda-1203427186/ |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref> \"Chapter 4\" director Bryce Dallas Howard said it was challenging directing emotional scenes between Omera and the Mandalorian because he always wears a helmet, but that the scenes worked because \"Julia is deeply connected to her emotions and you can just feel them on her face.\"<ref name=\"Miller1203\">{{cite news |last=Miller |first=Liz Shannon |title=Bryce Dallas Howard Screamed When She First Saw The Mandalorian's Baby Yoda |work=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]] |date=December 3, 2019 |url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/12/the-mandalorian-bryce-dallas-howard-sanctuary-baby-yoda.html |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref> Brendan Wayne, a body double for the Mandalorian character, said his scenes with Jones were so emotional that they made him cry.<ref>{{cite news |last=Miller |first=Liz Shannon |title=Meet the Man Beneath the Mandalorian's Armor |date=December 9, 2019 |url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/12/the-mandalorian-double-brendan-wayne-interview.html |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref> The character of Omera has received positive to mixed reviews from critics.{{#tag:ref|Bryan Young of ''/Film'' said Omera \"steals every scene she's in\" and had such excellent chemistry with the Mandalorian that it \"truly hurts\" when he cannot stay with her at the end of the episode.<ref name=\"Young1129\" /> ''Forbes'' writer Erik Kane described Omera as a \"great new female character introduced into a show that's been mostly men\", and said he wanted to learn more about the character.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kain |first=Erik |title='The Mandalorian' Episode 4 Recap And Review: The 'Star Wars' We Were Looking For |work=[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2019/11/29/the-mandalorian-episode-4-review-this-is-the-star-wars-we-were-waiting-for/ |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref> ''Vulture'' writer Liz Shannon Miller said Omera is a familiar archetype, but she appreciated that the character took a leadership role in the village and during the fighting scenes, and that she was not reduced to a background role due to her gender.<ref name=\"Miller1203\" /> Not all reviews were positive. Kathryn VanArendonk, also of ''Vulture'', wrote that Omera had \"zero characterization except that she is a good, protective mother\".<ref>{{cite news |last=VanArendonk |first=Kathryn |title=''The Mandalorian'' Doesn't Care About Diapers |work=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]] |date=January 3, 2020 |url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/01/the-mandalorian-parenting-fatherhood-archetype.html |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref> Anthony Gramuglia of ''Comic Book Resources'' wrote that some fans criticized Omera and the presence of other strong women in ''The Mandalorain'' because they felt it was \"forced diversity\". Gramuglia said these objections were [[Misogyny|misogynist]] and \"patently ridiculous\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Gramuglia |first=Anthony |title=The Mandalorian: Cara Dune Triggers Outrage By Being Female in Star Wars |work=[[Comic Book Resources]] |date=December 3, 2019 |url=https://www.cbr.com/the-mandalorian-cara-dune-star-wars-outrage/ |accessdate=January 31, 2020}}</ref>|group=\"nb\"}}\n\n===Winta===\nWinta is the young daughter of Omera, living in a village on Sorgan in \"Chapter 4: Sanctuary\".<ref name=\"Romain1115\" /><ref name=\"White1202\" /> She develops a close friendship with the Child after the Mandalorian brings him to the village.<ref name=\"Kirby1129\" /><ref name=\"Romain1115\" /><ref name=\"Phipps1129\">{{cite news |last=Phipps |first=Keith |title=''The Mandalorian'' Recap: Two and a Half Samurai |work=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/11/the-mandalorian-recap-chapter-4-sanctuary.html |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref> Winta is portrayed by Isla Farris.<ref name=\"Phipps1129\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Dumaraog |first=Ana |title=The Mandalorian Episode 4 Has A Hidden Time Jump |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-show-time-jump-weeks-episode-4/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Howell |first=Noah |title=TV Review: 'The Mandalorian' - 'Chapter Three: The Sin' & 'Chapter Four: Sanctuary' |work=[[University of North Carolina at Charlotte|Niner Times]] |date=December 5, 2019 |url=https://www.ninertimes.com/arts_and_entertainment/tv-review-the-mandalorian---chapter-three-the-sin/article_0d5bd648-173e-11ea-a929-dbf3d637b50c.html |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Caben and Stoke===\nCaben and Stoke are krill farmers in a Sorgan village in \"Chapter 4: Sanctuary\".<ref name=\"Thomas1230\" /><ref name=\"Didymus1129\">{{cite news |last=Didymus |first=John Thomas |title=Comedian Eugene Cordero on The Mandalorian: Who is actor who played Krill villager Stoke? |work=[[Monsters and Critics]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/smallscreen/comedian-eugene-cordero-on-the-mandalorian-who-is-actor-who-played-krill-villager-stoke/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref> The two hire the Mandalorian to provide protection from Klatooinian raiders attacking the village.<ref name=\"Didymus1129\" /><ref name=\"Silliman1129\">{{cite news |last=Silliman |first=Brian |title=Big details about the Mandalorian, Baby Yoda, and Gina Carano emerge in The Mandalorian ep. 4 |work=[[Syfy|Syfy Wire]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/mandalorian-chapter-4-baby-yoda-gina-carano-details-emerge |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Lindberg1129\">{{cite news |last=Lindbergh |first=Ben |title='The Mandalorian,' Chapter 4: How Can Mando and Baby Yoda Hide From Hunters Who Always Know Where They Are? |work=[[The Ringer (website)|The Ringer]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://www.theringer.com/mandalorian/2019/11/29/20988035/mandalorian-chapter-4-recap-sanctuary-baby-yoda-sorgan |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref> Caben is portrayed by actor and comedian Asif Ali,<ref name=\"Didymus1129\" /><ref name=\"McHenry0106\" /><ref name=\"Miller1129\">{{cite news |last=Miller |first=Liz Shannon |title=''The Mandalorian'' gets even more Western in a standalone adventure |work=[[The A.V. Club]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://tv.avclub.com/the-mandalorian-gets-even-more-western-in-a-stand-alone-1840097335 |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref> and Stoke is played by actor and comedian [[Eugene Cordero]].<ref name=\"Didymus1129\" /><ref name=\"Miller1129\" /> The two were included on ''Vulture''{{'}}s list of the show's 15 best cameo appearances from season one, in which writer Jackson McHenry described them as \"a delightful pair of goofy villagers\".<ref name=\"McHenry0106\" />\n\n===Riot Mar===\nRiot Mar is a bounty hunter who attempts to recover the Child from the Mandalorian in  \"Chapter 5: The Gunslinger\".<ref name=\"Lussier1206\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=The Mandalorian Season 1 Episode 5 Review: The Gunslinger |work=TV Fanatic |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://www.tvfanatic.com/shows/the-mandalorian/episodes/season-1/the-gunslinger/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Elfring |first=Mat |title=The Mandalorian Episode 5: 12 Star Wars Easter Eggs And References You May Have Missed |work=[[GameSpot]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/the-mandalorian-episode-5-12-star-wars-easter-eggs/2900-3256/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref> Riot pilots a [[List of Star Wars starfighters|starfighter]] and attacks the Mandalorian's ship, but is killed by the Mandalorian after a brief [[dogfight]].<ref name=\"Snowden1206\" /><ref name=\"Gullickson1206\">{{cite news |last=Gullickson |first=Brad |title='The Mandalorian' Explained: Chapter Five |work=[[Film School Rejects]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://filmschoolrejects.com/mandalorian-explained-chapter-five/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Bulten |first=Izak |title=Star Wars: The Mandalorian's 10 Most Savage Lines, Ranked |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=December 24, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/star-wars-the-mandalorian-most-savage-lines-ranked/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref> Riot Mar is portrayed by Rio Hackford.<ref name=\"Lussier1206\" /><ref name=\"Snowden1206\" /><ref name=\"Gullickson1206\" />\n\n===Peli Motto===\n[[Image:Amy Sedaris080112.jpg|thumb|upright|alt=A blonde woman wearing a black shirt and eyeglasses smiles and looks off-camera, holding her chin in her hand.|Peli Motto was portrayed by comedian and actress Amy Sedaris.]]\nPeli Motto is a mechanic who manages a spaceport on [[Tatooine]] in \"Chapter 5: The Gunslinger\".<ref name=\"Breznican1207\">{{cite news |last=Breznican |first=Anthony |title=Amy Sedaris cuddles Baby Yoda in new episode of ''The Mandalorian'' |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |date=December 7, 2019 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/12/the-mandalorian-chapter-5-boba-fett |accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Juzwiak1209\">{{cite news |last=Juzwiak |first=Rich |title=Great Performances: Amy Sedaris in ''The Mandalorian'' |work=[[Jezebel (website)|Jezebel]] |date=December 9, 2019 |url=https://themuse.jezebel.com/great-performances-amy-sedaris-in-the-mandalorian-1840317549 |accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref> The Mandalorian hires her to repair his ship,<ref name=\"Lussier1206\" /> and she also comes to take care of the Child.<ref name=\"VanArendonk1227\">{{cite news |last1=VanArendonk |first1=Kathryn |last2=McHenry |first2=Jackson |last3=Chaney |first3=Jen |title=Just the Baby Yoda Parts of ''The Mandalorian'' |work=[[New York (magazine)#Digital expansion and blogs|Vulture]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://www.vulture.com/article/baby-yoda-gifs-the-mandalorian.html |accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Enlow1209\">{{cite news |last=Enlow |first=Courtney |title=Chosen One of the Day: Amy Sedaris, the Momdalorian |work=[[Syfy|Syfy Wire]] |date=December 9, 2019 |url=https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/chosen-one-of-the-day-amy-sedaris-the-momdalorian |accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Keane1207\">{{cite news |last=Keane |first=Sean |title=The Mandalorian episode 5 recap: Baby Yoda travels to an iconic planet |work=[[CNET]] |date=December 7, 2019 |url=https://www.cnet.com/news/the-mandalorian-episode-5-the-gunslinger-recap-baby-yoda-travels-to-an-iconic-planet/ |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref> The bounty hunter Toro Calican briefly takes Peli and the Child as hostages in an unsuccessful attempt to abduct the Mandalorian.<ref name=\"Lussier1206\" /><ref name=\"Snowden1206\">{{cite news |last=Snowden |first=Scott |title='The Mandalorian' Episode 5 Visits a Well-Known World in the 'Star Wars' Universe |work=[[Space.com]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://www.space.com/star-wars-mandalorian-episode-5-review.html |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"VanArendonk1227\" /> Peli is portrayed by actress and comedian [[Amy Sedaris]],<ref name=\"Schedeen1227\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Paskin |first=Willa |title=The TV Club, 2019 |work=[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]] |date=December 12, 2019 |url=https://slate.com/culture/2019/12/tv-club-2019-mandalorian-baby-yoda.html |accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref> who had previously worked with ''The Mandalorian'' creator Jon Favreau on the film ''[[Elf (film)|Elf]]'' (2003).<ref>{{cite news |last=Romano |first=Evan |title=Amy Sedaris Made the Latest Comedy Cameo in ''The Mandalorian'' |work=[[Men's Health]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/a30147473/the-mandalorian-amy-sedaris-peli-motto/ |accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref> Sedaris said she enjoyed working with the animatronic Child puppet, which she said made everyone on the set happy: \"The minute you looked into Baby Yoda's eyes you just got lost.\"<ref name=\"Galindo1213\" /> The character and Sedaris' performance drew acclaim from fans and reviewers,{{#tag:ref| ''[[Jezebel (website)|Jezebel]]'' writer Rich Juzwiak called Sedaris' performance \"a gift\" and \"equal parts surprise and delight\", saying Sedaris brought her comedic idiosyncracies to the role.<ref name=\"Juzwiak1209\" /> Sean Keane of [[CNET]] said Sedaris was \"excellent\" as Peli, writing that she \"oozes charisma\" and displayed general warmth in her scenes with the Child.<ref name=\"Keane1207\" /> ''Vulture'' writer Jackson McHenry said the character was effective because she bears similarities to Sedaris' real-life persona, including her \"semi-ironic detachment and amusement\".<ref name=\"McHenry0106\" /> Keith Phipps, also of ''Vulture'', said Peli was a multifaceted character, showing sympathy for the Child while simultaneously appearing shrewd and vaguely threatening while negotiating with the Mandalorian.<ref name=\"Phipps1206\" /> Jason Wiese of ''CinemaBlend'' described Peli as \"joyously funny\" and said she would enjoy seeing a spin-off series focusing specifically on her.<ref>{{cite news |last=Wiese |first=Jason |title=5 Mandalorian Star Wars Spin-Off TV Shows We'd Love To See |work=CinemaBlend |date=February 17, 2020 |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/television/2490158/mandalorian-star-wars-spin-off-tv-shows-wed-love-to-see |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref> Rachel Leishman of ''[[Dan Abrams#The Mary Sue|The Mary Sue]]'' said she loved Sedaris' appearance, saying the actress brought \"the Amy Sedaris energy we know and love\" to the part.<ref name=\"Leishman1206\" /> ''Gizmodo'' writer Germain Lussier called Sedaris' casting another example of the \"kind of odd, yet wonderful intersection of ''Star Wars'' and comedy\" prevelent in ''The Mandalorian''.<ref name=\"Lussier1206\">{{cite news |last=Lussier |first=Germain |title=The Latest Mandalorian Had Maybe a Little Too Much Fan Service for Its Own Good |work=[[Gizmodo]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/the-latest-mandalorian-had-maybe-a-little-too-much-fan-1840243870 |accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref> Many fans and reviewers complimented Peli Motto's wig,<ref name=\"Leishman1206\" /><ref name=\"Phipps1206\">{{cite news |last=Phipps |first=Keith |title=''The Mandalorian'' Recap: Bounty Flaw |work=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/12/the-mandalorian-recap-episode-5-the-gunslinger.html |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Enlow1209\" /> while others said her hair and jumpsuit-like costume bore similarities to ''[[Alien (franchise)|Alien]]'' franchise protagonist [[Ellen Ripley]].<ref name=\"Breznican1207\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Bundel |first=Ani |title=Who Is Amy Sedaris' 'Mandalorian' Character? She Looks Familiar |work=[[Elite Daily]] |date=December 9, 2019 |url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/who-is-amy-sedaris-mandalorian-character-she-looks-familiar-19435305 |accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=VanArendonk |first=Kathryn |title=''The Mandalorian'' Doesn't Care About Diapers |work=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]] |date=January 3, 2020 |url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/01/the-mandalorian-parenting-fatherhood-archetype.html |accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref> Peli Motto was in included ''[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]]''{{'}}s list of the show's 15 best cameo appearances from season one,<ref name=\"McHenry0106\" /> and her costume was ranked fifth on a ''Screen Rant'' list of the ten best costumes in the first season of ''The Mandalorian''.<ref name=\"Atkin0108\" />|group=\"nb\"}} so much so that Sedaris became a [[Twitter trends|trending topic]] on Twitter after the episode first became available.<ref name=\"Galindo1213\">{{cite news |last=Gaindo |first=Brian |title=We Asked Amy Sedaris About Baby Yoda Because How Could We Not |work=[[Buzzfeed]] |date= December 13, 2019 |url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/briangalindo/we-talked-to-amy-sedaris-about-baby-yoda-and-the-holidays |accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Leishman1206\">{{cit news |last=Leishman |first=Rachel |title=Amy Sedaris on ''The Mandalorian'' Made Everyone Lose Their Minds |work=[[Dan Abrams#The Mary Sue|The Mary Sue]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://www.themarysue.com/amy-sedaris-the-mandalorian/ |accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Prahl |first=Amanda |title= The Mandalorian: Twitter Has Decided Amy Sedaris Holding Baby Yoda Is the Best Part of 2019 |work=[[PopSugar]] |date=December 9, 2019 |url=https://www.popsugar.com/entertainment/reactions-to-amy-sedaris-on-mandalorian-46990071 |accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Toro Calican===\nToro Calican was a young bounty hunter who encountered the Mandalorian in episode \"Chapter 5: The Gunslinger\".<ref name=\"Sherlock0120\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Dumaraog |first=Ana |title=The Mandalorian Finally Became The Show Disney Promised |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=December 16, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-show-good-disney-marketing/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Raymond |first=Nicholas |title=Star Wars Theory: The Mandalorian's Mystery Man Is Boba Fett |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=December 10, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/star-wars-mandalorian-episode-5-ending-man-boba-fett-theory/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref> He recruits the Mandalorian's help capturing the assassin Fennec Shand. It is Toro's first bounty hunting assignment, and he hopes it will help him get into the Bounty Hunters' Guild.<ref name=\"Snowden1206\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Gallagher |first=Caitlin |title=Who Is The Person At The End Of 'The Mandalorian' Episode 5? 6 Theories Promise Another Villain |work=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://www.bustle.com/p/who-is-the-person-at-the-end-of-the-mandalorian-episode-5-6-theories-promise-another-villain-19431233 |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Bundel |first=Ani |title='The Mandalorian' Season 1, Episode 5 Cliffhanger Has Fans Theorizing Up A Storm |work=[[Elite Daily]] |date=December 9, 2019 |url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/the-mandalorian-season-1-episode-5-cliffhanger-has-fans-theorizing-up-a-storm-19435918 |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref> Toro later double-crosses the Mandalorian and attempts to turn him over to the Guild, but is instead shot and killed by the Mandalorian.<ref name=\"Snowden1206\" /><ref name=\"Romano1206\">{{cite news |last=Romano |first=Evan |title=''The Mandalorian'' Introduced Fennec Shand, But Her Star Wars Story Is Just Beginning |work=[[Men's Health]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/a30148400/the-mandalorian-fennec-shand/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Mitovich |first=Matt Webb |title=''Mandalorian'' Recap: How You Tatooine? |work=[[TVLine]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://tvline.com/2019/12/06/the-mandalorian-recap-season-1-episode-5-gunslinger/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref> Toro Calican is portrayed by [[Jake Cannavale]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Brown |first=Tracy |title=The Baby Yoda show ends today. To celebrate, we ranked his scene partners |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/tv/story/2019-12-27/baby-yoda-mandalorian-best-worst |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Britt |first=Ryan |title=Disney+ Just Revealed Luke Skywalker's Biggest Mistake |work=[[Yahoo!]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/disney-just-revealed-luke-skywalkers-121947863.html |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Dwilson |first=Stephanie Dube |title=\u2018The Mandalorian\u2019 Episode 5 Easter Eggs: Mos Eisley, a Red Droid & More |work=[[Heavy.com]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://heavy.com/entertainment/2019/12/mandalorian-episode-5-mos-eisley/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref> The character received mixed to negative reviews from critics.{{#tag:ref|Toro Calican made ''Vulture''{{'}}s list of the show's 15 best cameo appearances from season one. ''Vulture'' writer Jackson McHenry complimented Cannavale, but said the character was \"not the most glamorous part\".<ref name=\"McHenry0106\" /> Germain Lussier of ''[[Gizmodo]]'' called the introduction of a character at the start of his bounty hunting career a \"very intriguing twist\".<ref name=\"Lussier1206\" /> ''[[Collider (website)|Collider]]'' writer Vinne Mancuso called Toro a \"strange character\", but ultimately an inconsequential one since he was killed so quickly.<ref name=\"Mancuso1208\">{{cite news |last=Mancuso |first=Vinnie |title='The Mandalorian' Guide, Week 5: Every Question We Have After \"The Gunslinger\" |work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |date=December 8, 2019 |url=https://collider.com/the-mandalorian-episode-5-theories/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref> Gregory Lawrence, also of ''Collider'', describing him as a \"[[Romantic comedy|romcom]] villainous douche\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Lawrence |first=Gregory |title=The Funniest 'Mandalorian' Jokes and Memes of the Week |work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |date=December 9, 2019 |url=https://collider.com/the-mandalorian-episode-5-theories/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref> Tyler Hersko of ''[[IndieWire]]'' called Toro a \"petulant\" character less appealing than other antagonists on ''The Mandalorian''.<ref>{{cite news |last=Hersko |first=Tyler |title='The Mandalorian' Review: The Series' One Plot Idea Wears Out Its Welcome in Episode 6 |work=[[IndieWire]] |date=December 13, 2019 |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/12/mandalorian-episode-6-review-1202197284/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref> ''Screen Rant'' writer Jessie Atkin called Toro a \"poor caricature\" with \"annoying\" dialogue, and criticized the show for recycling old ideas like him instead of exploring new territory. Atkin wrote: \"Toro Calican was obviously supposed to be a lame knock off of [[Han Solo]], haha, we get the joke, but boy is it one fans don't need to see again.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Atkin |first=Jessie |title=5 Things We Want to See in The Mandalorian Season 2 (& 5 That We Don't) |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=January 2, 2020 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-second-season-predictions-speculation/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref>|group=\"nb\"}} Cannavale later attracted media attention for publicly criticizing the [[Star Wars sequel trilogy|sequel trilogy]] film ''[[Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker]]'' (2019) on social media, calling it \"hands down the worst ''Star Wars'' movie\".<ref>{{cite news |title=One 'Mandalorian' Actor Called 'The Rise of Skywalker' an 'Absolute F*cking Failure' |work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]] |date=December 23, 2019 |url=https://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2019/12/the-mandalorian-actor-called-the-rise-of-skywalker-absolute-failure |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Carbone |first=Gina |title=The Mandalorian Actor Slams Rise Of Skywalker As 'The Worst Star Wars Movie' |work=Cinema Blend |date=December 21, 2019 |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2487292/the-mandalorian-actor-slams-rise-of-skywalker-as-the-worst-star-wars-movie |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Joyner |first=Alfred |title='The Mandalorian' actor calls 'The Rise of Skywalker' 'hands down the worst Star Wars movie' and 'an absolute f***ing failure' |work=[[Newsweek]] |date=December 21, 2019 |url=https://www.newsweek.com/mandalorian-star-wars-rise-skywalker-worst-reviews-failure-rotten-tomatoes-1478662 |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Fennec Shand===\n[[Image:Ming-Na Wen by Gage Skidmore 2.jpg|thumb|upright|alt=A woman in a patterned dress sits in a chair and holds a microphone while looking off-camera.|Fennec Shand is portrayed by Ming-Na Wen, and is the first major ''Star Wars'' villain character portrayed by an Asian actress.]]\n{{Main|Fennec Shand}}\nFennec Shand is an assassin and mercenary for the galaxy's top crime syndicates,<ref name=\"Gemmill1206\">{{cite news |last=Gemmill |first=Allie |title=Is Fennec Shand really dead? 'Mandalorian' Episode 5 clues suggest otherwise |work=[[Inverse (website)|Inverse]] |date=December 6, 2019 |url=https://www.inverse.com/article/61522-mandalorian-episode-5-fennec-shand-alive-dead-spoilers-theory |accessdate=February 22, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Breznican1104\">{{cite news |last=Breznican |first=Anthony |author-link=Anthony Breznican |title=First Look: Ming-Na Wen's ''Star Wars'' Assassin From ''The Mandalorian'' |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |date=November 4, 2019 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/11/ming-na-wen-the-mandalorian-star-wars-fennec-shand |accessdate=February 22, 2020}}</ref> who is sought by Toro Calican for his first bounty hunting assignment.<ref name=\"Snowden1206\" /> Calican catches Fennec with assistance from the Mandalorian.<ref name=\"Lussier1206\" /> When Fennec tries to convince Toro to free her so they could capture the Mandalorian and deliver him to the Bounty Hunters' Guild, Toro instead kills Fennec and seeks to capture the Mandalorian himself.<ref name=\"Lussier1206\" />\n\nPortrayed by actress [[Ming-Na Wen]],<ref>{{cite news |last=Snowden |first=Scott |title='The Mandalorian' Finale is an Electrifying End to Season 1 |work=[[Space.com]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://www.space.com/star-wars-the-mandalorian-episode-8-review.html |accessdate=January 20, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112033204/https://www.space.com/star-wars-the-mandalorian-episode-8-review.html |archive-date=January 12, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Reichert |first=Corinne |title=The Mandalorian release schedule on Disney Plus has leaked |work=[[CNET]] |date=November 4, 2019 |url=https://www.cnet.com/news/the-mandalorian-release-schedule-on-disney-plus-has-leaked/ |accessdate=February 25, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Schedeen |first=Jesse |title=The Mandalorian Cast: Every Character and Cameo in Season 1 |work=[[IGN]] |date=December 27, 2019 |url=https://sea.ign.com/star-wars-tv-series/156188/feature/the-mandalorian-cast-every-character-and-cameo-in-season-1 |accessdate=February 25, 2020}}</ref> Fennec Shand is the first major ''Star Wars'' villain character portrayed by an Asian actress. Elements of the character's personality were inspired by characteristics of the [[fennec fox]], including its trickiness, stealthiness, maneuverability, and ability to survive.<ref name=\"Breznican1104\" /> The fox also influenced the design of Fennec's costume and hairstyle. Costume designer Joseph Porro incorporated orange accents into Fennec's black costume, and Wen recommended the character's hair include braids inspired by the fennec fox.<ref name=\"Breznican1104\" /> Fennec Shand has been received positively by reviewers and fans alike, and has been described as a fan favorite.<ref name=\"McHenry0106\">{{cite news |last=McHenry |first=Jackson |title=''The Mandalorian''{{'}}s 15 Best Cameo Appearances, Ranked |work=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]] |date=January 6, 2020 |url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/01/the-mandalorian-best-comedian-cameos.html |accessdate=February 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200108213638/https://www.vulture.com/2020/01/the-mandalorian-best-comedian-cameos.html |archive-date=January 8, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Romano1206\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Bulten |first=Izak |title=Star Wars: MBTI\u00a9 Of The Mandalorian Characters |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=January 6, 2020 |url=https://screenrant.com/star-wars-mandalorian-characters-mbti/ |accessdate=February 25, 2020}}</ref> Several reviewers felt the character was eliminated too quickly and did not get the chance to live up to her potential,<ref name=\"Gemmill1206\" /><ref>{{cite podcast |last=Robinson |first=Joanna |url=https://open.spotify.com/episode/15ud0Bip0vDJDywLJam8Ig?si=vlgP0ZzIQn6Kr2Kods5LLw |title=Still Watching: The Mandalorian \u2014 \"Chapter Five: The Gunslinger\" with Bryce Dallas Howard and Ming Na Wen |publisher=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |date=December 6, 2019 |access-date=January 29, 2020 |time=33:43\u201334:22 |quote=We were both really excited that Ming-Na Wen was on this show. If this is the end of her, which it kind of seems like it is, if this is just like a short appearance... I would've really dug like a whole long night with the Mandalorian and Fennec Shand, like, sitting up against some rocks, trading barbs or something like that. I think there's real potential for a character like this. I mean, The Mandalorian's a very action-heavy show, but I really feel like with a performer like Ming-Na Wen, with a character as coiled, there's like this coiled power in her, and I feel like we could've gotten some fun mind games out of her.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Libbey |first=Dirk |title=The Mandalorian: 10 Biggest Questions After Season 1 |work=CinemaBlend |date=January 11, 2020 |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/television/2488134/the-mandalorian-biggest-questions-after-season-1 |accessdate=February 22, 2020}}</ref> and some critics have speculated that the character could still be alive.<ref name=\"Gemmill1206\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Floorwalker |first=Mike |title=Who was the person at the end of The Mandalorian chapter 5? |work=[[ZergNet|Looper]] |date=December 10, 2019 |url=https://www.looper.com/178493/who-was-the-person-at-the-end-of-the-mandalorian-chapter-5/ |accessdate=February 22, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Stefansky |first=Emma |title= Everything We Know About 'The Mandalorian' Season 2 |work=[[Thrillist]] |date=February 14, 2020 |url=https://www.thrillist.com/entertainment/nation/the-mandalorian-season-2-release-date |accessdate=February 25, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Ranzar Malk===\nRanzar \"Ran\" Malk is the leader of a group of mercenaries that operate out of a space station in \"Chapter 6: The Prisoner\".<ref name=\"Moran1215\" /><ref name=\"Lindbergh1213\">{{cite news |last=Lindbergh |first=Ben |title='The Mandalorian' Chapter 6: Are We Ever Going to See What\u2019s Under That Helmet? |work=[[The Ringer (website)|The Ringer]] |date=December 13, 2019 |url=https://www.theringer.com/tv/2019/12/13/21020802/mandalorian-season-1-episode-6-the-prisoner-review-recap |accessdate=February 13, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Martin1125\" /> He develops a plan for his crew to infiltrate a [[New Republic (Star Wars)|New Republic]] prison ship and rescue Qin, an imprisoned Twi'lek.<ref name=\"Lindbergh1213\" /><ref name=\"Snowden1213\" /> After the mission, Ran tries to have the Mandalorian killed,<ref name=\"Snowden1213\" /><ref name=\"Kain1213\" /> but instead his space station is attacked by New Republic X-wing fighters, which were led there by the Mandalorian.<ref name=\"Lindbergh1213\" /> Ran is portrayed by [[Mark Boone Junior]].<ref name=\"Thomas1230\" /><ref name=\"Schedeen1227\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Melrose |first=Kevin |title=The Mandalorian Takes Shots At Stormtrooper Aim \u2013 and Jar Jar Binks |work=[[Comic Book Resources]] |date=December 13, 2019 |url=https://www.cbr.com/mandalorian-stormtrooper-jar-jar-binks-jokes/ |accessdate=February 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191214125127/https://www.cbr.com/mandalorian-stormtrooper-jar-jar-binks-jokes/ |archive-date=December 14, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Fans reacted positively to Ran's character and Boone's performance,<ref>{{cite news |last=Levine |first=Daniel S. |title='Sons of Anarchy' Fans Weigh in on Mark Boone Junior's Appearance on 'The Mandalorian' |work=[[CBS Interactive|Pop Culture Media]] |date=December 14, 2019 |url=https://popculture.com/tv-shows/2019/12/13/sons-of-anarchy-fans-weigh-in-mark-boone-junior-the-mandalorian/ |accessdate=February 17, 2020}}</ref> and the character was included on ''[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]]''{{'}}s list of the show's 15 best cameo appearances from season one.<ref name=\"McHenry0106\" />\n\n===Mayfeld===\n[[Image:Bill Burr by Gage Skidmore.jpg|thumb|upright|alt=A bald man with red and gray facial hair smiles and looks off-camera.|Comedian Bill Burr, who was not a fan of ''Star Wars'' and had previously mocked the franchise, portrayed Mayfeld.]]\n{{Main|Mayfeld}}\nMayfeld is a former Imperial [[sharpshooter]] who leads a crew of Ranzar \"Ran\" Malk's mercenaries in their attempt to rescue Qin from a New Republic prison transport ship.<ref name=\"Baver0210\" /><ref name=\"Britt1213\">{{cite news |last=Britt |first=Ryan |title=Anakin Skywalker and three more cameos you missed in 'Mandalorian' episode 6 |work=[[Inverse (website)|Inverse]] |date=December 13, 2019 |url=https://www.inverse.com/article/61702-mandalorian-cameos-x-wing-pilots-dave-filoni-matt-lanter-anakin-skywalker-clancy-brown-natalia-tena-richard-ayoade |accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Babu |first=Armaan |title='The Mandalorian' finally makes it official: The Stormtroopers do have the worst aim in the galaxy |work=MEA WorldWide |date=December 13, 2019 |url=https://meaww.com/the-mandalorian-makes-it-official-stormtroopers-worst-aim-galaxy-disney |accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> He uses two [[Blaster (Star Wars)|blaster]] pistols, as well as a third blaster controlled by a droid arm attached to his backpack.<ref name=\"Pham1231\" /><ref name=\"Sherlock0120\">{{cite news |last=Sherlock |first=Ben |title=The Mandalorian: 10 Characters We Hope To See Return In Season 2 |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=January 20, 2020 |url=https://screenrant.com/star-wars-mandalorian-characters-want-return-season-two-disney-plus/ |accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Skrebels1213\">{{cite news |last=Skrebels |first=Joe |title=The Mandalorian: Episode 6 Review |work=[[IGN]] |date=January 3, 2020 |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/12/13/the-mandalorian-episode-6-review |accessdate=February 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200101035518/https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/12/13/the-mandalorian-episode-6-review |archive-date=January 1, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Mayfeld clashes repeatedly with the Mandalorian during the mission,<ref name=\"Lindbergh1213\" /><ref name=\"Britt1213\" /><ref name=\"Jackson1216\">{{cite news |last=Jackson |first=Brad |title='The Mandalorian' Episode Six Is Packed With Guest Stars And Other Delights |work=[[The Federalist (website)|The Federalist]] |date=December 16, 2019 |url=https://thefederalist.com/2019/12/16/the-mandalorian-episode-six-is-packed-with-guest-stars-and-other-delights/ |accessdate=February 13, 2020}}</ref> and ultimately attempts to betray him,<ref name=\"Lindbergh1213\" /><ref name=\"Jackson1216\" /> but instead the Mandalorian incapacitates Mayfeld and locks him in a cell on the transport.<ref name=\"Sherlock0120\" /><ref name=\"Lindbergh1213\" />\n\nMayfeld is portrayed by actor and comedian [[Bill Burr]],<ref name=\"Moran1215\" /><ref name=\"Dumaraog1214\">{{cite news |last=Dumaraog |first=Ana |title=The Mandalorian's Surprise Episode 6 Cameos Explained |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=December 14, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/mandalorian-episode-6-ending-xwing-pilots-cameos-explained/ |accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Britt |first=Ryan |title='Last Jedi' 'Mandalorian' Easter egg may explain First Order origins |work=[[Inverse (website)|Inverse]] |date=December 15, 2019 |url=https://www.inverse.com/article/61712-mandalorian-theory-episode-6-canto-bight-last-jedi-first-order-rise-of-skywalker |accessdate=February 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200115052416/https://www.inverse.com/article/61712-mandalorian-theory-episode-6-canto-bight-last-jedi-first-order-rise-of-skywalker |archive-date=January 15, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> who was not a fan of ''Star Wars'' and repeatedly mocked the franchise and its fans before he accepted the role.<ref>{{cite news |last=Joest |first=Mick |title=The Mandalorian Actor Admits He Never Liked Star Wars And Mocked Every Movie |work=CinemaBlend |date=September 22, 2019 |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2480735/the-mandalorian-actor-admits-he-never-liked-star-wars-and-mocked-every-movie |accessdate=February 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125162225/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2480735/the-mandalorian-actor-admits-he-never-liked-star-wars-and-mocked-every-movie |archive-date=January 25, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Jon Favreau offered the part to Burr, believing his past criticism of the franchise would make his casting that much more amusing.<ref>{{cite news |last=Romano |first=Evan |title=How ''Star Wars'' Hater Bill Burr Got Cast In ''The Mandalorian'' |work=[[Men's Health]] |date=December 13, 2019 |url=https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/a29501279/the-mandalorian-bill-burr/ |accessdate=February 15, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191214161302/https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/a29501279/the-mandalorian-bill-burr/ |archive-date=December 14, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Scarano |first=Genevieve |title='The Mandalorian' Star Bill Burr Says He Was Never Into 'Star Wars' Movies |work=[[Geek.com]] |date=September 18, 2019 |url=https://www.geek.com/television/the-mandalorian-star-bill-burr-says-he-was-never-into-star-wars-movies-1804459/ |accessdate=February 15, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920201651/https: