is-yogi-right-hand-man-who-led-crackdown-on-caa-protests/368170/|work=[[ThePrint]] |date=20 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"f\">{{cite news |title= \u0928\u093e\u0917\u0930\u093f\u0915\u0924\u093e \u0915\u093e\u0928\u0942\u0928: \u0905\u0935\u0928\u0940\u0936 \u0905\u0935\u0938\u094d\u0925\u0940 \u0928\u0947 \u091f\u0947\u0932\u0940\u0915\u0949\u092e \u0935\u093f\u092d\u093e\u0917 \u0915\u094b \u0932\u093f\u0916\u093e \u092a\u0924\u094d\u0930, 45 \u0918\u0902\u091f\u0947 \u0924\u0915 \u092c\u0902\u0926 \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e\u090f\u0902 \u0907\u0902\u091f\u0930\u0928\u0947\u091f \u0938\u0947\u0935\u093e\u090f\u0902 |url=https://www.abpganga.com/aapka-pradesh/principal-secretary-home-avnish-kumar-awasthi-letter-to-telecom-department-to-suspend-internet-services-for-45-hours-36669|work=[[NDTV]] |date=20 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n\n==Personal life==\nAwanish Kumar Awasthi is married to well known and Padma Shri (2016) awardees Indian folk singer [[Malini Awasthi]] and have one daughter Ananya.<ref name=\"d\">{{cite news |title= \u092a\u094d\u0930\u092e\u0941\u0916 \u0938\u091a\u093f\u0935 \u0917\u0943\u0939 \u0935 \u092e\u093e\u0932\u093f\u0928\u0940 \u0905\u0935\u0938\u094d\u0925\u0940 \u0915\u0940 \u092c\u0947\u091f\u0940 \u0915\u0940 \u0936\u093e\u0926\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092a\u0939\u0941\u0902\u091a\u0947 \u092e\u0941\u0916\u094d\u092f\u092e\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0935 \u0930\u093e\u091c\u094d\u092f\u092a\u093e\u0932, \u0926\u0940 \u0936\u0941\u092d\u0915\u093e\u092e\u0928\u093e\u090f\u0902 |url=https://www.amarujala.com/photo-gallery/lucknow/chief-secretary-home-awanish-awasthi-and-malini-awasthi-daughter-marriage |work=[[Amar Ujala]] |date=13 November 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"e\">{{cite news |title= \u092e\u0936\u0939\u0942\u0930 \u0917\u093e\u092f\u093f\u0915\u093e \u092e\u093e\u0932\u093f\u0928\u0940 \u0905\u0935\u0938\u094d\u200d\u0925\u0940 \u0915\u0947 IAS \u092a\u0924\u093f \u0905\u0935\u0928\u0940\u0936 \u0915\u0941\u092e\u093e\u0930 \u0939\u094b\u0902\u0917\u0947 CM \u092f\u094b\u0917\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0927\u093e\u0928 \u0938\u091a\u093f\u0935! |url=https://khabar.ndtv.com/news/india/folk-singer-malini-awasthi-husband-avanish-kumar-awasthi-will-be-principal-secretary-of-up-cm-yogi-a-1678821 |work=[[NDTV]] |date=8 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Awanish Kumar Awasthi}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian civil servants]]\n[[Category:Indian Administrative Service officers]]\n[[Category:Indian government officials]]\n[[Category:People from Kanpur district]]\n", "name_user": "Pooja Shree Gaur", "label": "safe", "comment": "corrected URL", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Awanish_Kumar_Awasthi"}
{"title_page": "Elaine Valdov", "text_new": "\n\n'''Elaine Valdov''' is President and Founder of The International Institute for a Culture of Peace<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.superfutures.org/programs/un/schedule |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-09-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090420161030/http://www.superfutures.org/programs/un/schedule |archivedate=2009-04-20 }} </ref> As a peace and human rights activist and conflict resolution specialist, Valdov lectures internationally and is best known for her work in championing and building initiatives worldwide, in support of the [[UN Millennium Development Goals]] (MDGs) and [[UNESCO]]\u2019s<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unac.org/peacecp/decade/background.html|title=The International Decade for a Culture of Peace and Non-violence for the Children of the World (2001 to 2010) |accessdate=September 17, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090917190816/http://www.unac.org/peacecp/decade/background.html |archivedate=September 17, 2009 }}</ref> [[International Decade for the Promotion of a Culture of Peace and Non-Violence for the Children of the World]]. She has chaired task forces for women empowerment and gender equality; and founded \u201cYoga Peace Ambassadors\u201d to teach MDG humanitarian service options in Yoga Ashrams worldwide.\n\nValdov has held many NGO positions at UN Headquarters in New York, including:\n* Chair: Executive Committee of NGOs Affiliated with the [[United Nations Department of Public Information]] 1996-2000 (outreaching to civil society and NGOs worldwide, to enhance the partnerships between the United Nations, Governments and NGOs in addressing world challenges.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.un.org/dpi/ngosection/annualconfs/51/conf-programme.html|title=Non-Governmental Organization/DPI|website=Un.org|accessdate=20 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.un.org/dpi/ngosection/annualconfs/52/conf-programme.html|title=Non-Governmental Organization/DPI|website=Un.org|accessdate=20 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.un.org/dpi/ngosection/annualconfs/53/conf-schedule.html|title=Non-Governmental Organization/DPI|website=Un.org|accessdate=20 March 2016}}</ref>\n* Co-Convener: Seoul International Conference of NGOs: The Role of NGOs in the 21st Century.\n* Secretary General: Medical Assembly at the United Nations (focused on reversing the World Health Organization and World Bank\u2019s predicted world pandemic of cancer.)\n* Chair: NGO Committee on the [[University for Peace]].\n* VP, Member of Executive Committee and Advisory Committee to the UN Secretary General:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ngo.org/millennium/index.htm |title=Millennium NGO Forum \"The UN for the 21st Century\" |website=Ngo.org |date= |accessdate=2016-03-30}}</ref> As President of the DPI Executive Committee, Dr Valdov, was on the Millennum NGO Forum Advisory Committee to the UN Secretary General in 1997 and 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ngo.org/millennium/sld014.htm |title=PPT Slide |website=Ngo.org |date= |accessdate=2016-03-30}}</ref>\n\nShe has been a director of mental health facilities and a trauma counselor, with persons from countries around the world. Following September 11, Valdov was the director of the September 11 family relations and established programs in the US and abroad, helping families to deal with disasters, with special focus on helping widows and children who are caught in the midst of violence and terrorism. She further has worked with [[Lions Club International]], [[Rotary International]] and <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.faf.org/ |title=Friendship Ambassadors Foundation |website=Faf.org |date=2013-09-15 |accessdate=2016-03-30}}</ref> (FAF) in the creation and implementation of the post-September-11 programs of (\u201cFinding New Hope\u201d) and (\u201cUniversal Hug for Peace\u201d).\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090406043830/http://theworldwater.org/ The World Water Organization]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090615065105/http://www.theworldenergyforum.org/index.html The World Energy Forum]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Valdov, Elaine}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n'''Elaine Valdov''' is President and Founder of The International Institute for a Culture of Peace<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.superfutures.org/programs/un/schedule |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-09-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090420161030/http://www.superfutures.org/programs/un/schedule |archivedate=2009-04-20 }} </ref> As a peace and human rights activist and conflict resolution specialist, Valdov lectures internationally and is best known for her work in championing and building initiatives worldwide, in support of the [[UN Millennium Development Goals]] (MDGs) and [[UNESCO]]\u2019s<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unac.org/peacecp/decade/background.html|title=The International Decade for a Culture of Peace and Non-violence for the Children of the World (2001 to 2010) |accessdate=September 17, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090917190816/http://www.unac.org/peacecp/decade/background.html |archivedate=September 17, 2009 }}</ref> [[International Decade for the Promotion of a Culture of Peace and Non-Violence for the Children of the World]]. She has chaired task forces for women empowerment and gender equality; and founded \u201cYoga Peace Ambassadors\u201d to teach MDG humanitarian service options in Yoga Ashrams worldwide.\n\nValdov has held many NGO positions at UN Headquarters in New York, including:\n* Chair: Executive Committee of NGOs Affiliated with the [[United Nations Department of Public Information]](UNDPI) 1996-2000 (outreaching to civil society and NGOs worldwide, to enhance the partnerships between the United Nations, Governments and NGOs in addressing world challenges.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.un.org/dpi/ngosection/annualconfs/51/conf-programme.html|title=Non-Governmental Organization/DPI|website=Un.org|accessdate=20 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.un.org/dpi/ngosection/annualconfs/52/conf-programme.html|title=Non-Governmental Organization/DPI|website=Un.org|accessdate=20 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.un.org/dpi/ngosection/annualconfs/53/conf-schedule.html|title=Non-Governmental Organization/DPI|website=Un.org|accessdate=20 March 2016}}</ref>\n* Co-Convener: Seoul International Conference of NGOs: The Role of NGOs in the 21st Century.\n* Secretary General: Medical Assembly at the United Nations (focused on reversing the World Health Organization and World Bank\u2019s predicted world pandemic of cancer.)\n* Chair: NGO Committee on the [[University for Peace]].\n* VP, Member of Executive Committee and Advisory Committee to the UN Secretary General:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ngo.org/millennium/index.htm |title=Millennium NGO Forum \"The UN for the 21st Century\" |website=Ngo.org |date= |accessdate=2016-03-30}}</ref> As President of the DPI Executive Committee, Dr Valdov, was on the Millennum NGO Forum Advisory Committee to the UN Secretary General in 1997 and 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ngo.org/millennium/sld014.htm |title=PPT Slide |website=Ngo.org |date= |accessdate=2016-03-30}}</ref>\n\nShe has been a director of mental health facilities and a trauma counselor, with persons from countries around the world. Following September 11, Valdov was the director of the September 11 family relations and established programs in the US and abroad, helping families to deal with disasters, with special focus on helping widows and children who are caught in the midst of violence and terrorism. She further has worked with [[Lions Club International]], [[Rotary International]] and <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.faf.org/ |title=Friendship Ambassadors Foundation |website=Faf.org |date=2013-09-15 |accessdate=2016-03-30}}</ref> (FAF) in the creation and implementation of the post-September-11 programs of (\u201cFinding New Hope\u201d) and (\u201cUniversal Hug for Peace\u201d).\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090406043830/http://theworldwater.org/ The World Water Organization]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090615065105/http://www.theworldenergyforum.org/index.html The World Energy Forum]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Valdov, Elaine}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "name_user": "Ira Leviton", "label": "safe", "comment": "Deleted an unneeded abbreviation.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elaine_Valdov"}
{"title_page": "Huayi Brothers", "text_new": "{{About|the Chinese entertainment and media conglomerate|the South Korean subsidiary|Huayi Brothers (South Korean company)}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n|name             = Huayi Brothers Media Corporation<br/>\u534e\u8c0a\u5144\u5f1f\u4f20\u5a92\u96c6\u56e2\n|logo             = Huayi Brothers Media.jpg\n|logo_size        = 200px\n|type             = Public ([[Shenzhen Stock Exchange|SZSE]]:300027)\n|genre            = \n|fate             = August On China Vision\n|predecessor      = \n|successor        = \n|foundation       = 1994\n|founder          = [[Wang Zhongjun]], Wang Zhonglei\n|defunct          = \n|location_city    = [[Beijing]]\n|location_country = [[China]] \n|locations        = 1\n|key_people       = [[Wang Zhongjun]] (Chairman & [[CEO]]), Wang Zhonglei (President)\n|area_served      = China\n|industry         = {{nowrap|[[Entertainment]]}}\n|products         = Movies, television shows, music, movie theaters\n|services         = Talent representation for musicians and actors/actresses\n|revenue          = {{Increase}} CNY 892,000,000 (2011)\n|operating_income = \n|net_income       = \n|aum              = \n|assets           = \n|equity           = \n|owner            = Wang Zhongjun, Wang Zhonglei\n|num_employees    = \n|parent           = \n|divisions        = \n|subsid           = Huayi Brothers Film Investment Co., Ltd.<br/>Huayi Brothers TV Service Co., Ltd.<br/>Huayi Brothers Contemporary Culture Broker Co., Ltd.<br/>Huayi Brothers Music Co., Ltd.<br/>Huayi Brothers Advertising Co., Ltd.<br/>Huayi Brothers International Distribution Ltd<br>[[Huayi Brothers Korea|Huayi Brothers Korea Co., Ltd.]]\n|homepage         = {{URL|http://huayimedia.com}}\n|footnotes        = \n}}\n{{Infobox record label\n| name        = Huayi Brothers\n| image       = \n| founded     = 1994\n| defunct     = \n| founder     = [[Wang Zhongjun]], Wang Zhonglei\n| distributor = \n| genre       = [[Mandopop]]\n| country     = [[China]]\n| location    = [[Beijing]], [[China]]\n| url         = {{URL|ent.sina.com.cn/huayi}}\n| image_bg    = \n}}\n\n'''Huayi Brothers Media Corp.''' ({{zh|s=\u534e\u8c0a\u5144\u5f1f\u4f20\u5a92\u80a1\u4efd\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8|p=Hu\u00e1y\u00ec Xi\u014dngd\u00ec Chu\u00e1nm\u00e9i G\u01d4f\u00e8n Y\u01d2uxi\u00e0n G\u014dngs\u012b}}) is a Chinese multinational entertainment company that owns a [[film studio]], a television [[production company]], a [[talent agency]], a [[record label]], and a [[movie theater|movie theater chain]] founded in [[Beijing]] by brothers [[Wang Zhongjun]] and Wang Zhonglei in 1994. The company made world news on October 30, 2009 when the Shenzhen Stock Exchange [[ChiNext]] Board was halted, after HBMC's stock price reached 122.74 percent above its IPO price, to open at 63.66 yuan per share.<ref>{{cite web\n| title = All stocks trigger suspensions on China's Nasdaq-style board under price-rise rules on first day\n| url=http://english.people.com.cn/90001/90778/90859/6799005.html\n| accessdate = 12 June 2014}}</ref> Patrick Frater of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' called it \"China\u2019s largest private sector film conglomerate\".<ref name=Frater>{{cite web |url= https://variety.com/2015/film/asia/huayi-brothers-michael-uslan-pact-for-thunder-agents-franchise-1201615725/|title= China\u2019s Huayi Brothers Sets Superhero Franchise Pact With Michael Uslan|author= Patrick Frater|date= October 12, 2015|accessdate= October 14, 2015|work= [[variety.com]]}}</ref> In 2014, the company was the seventh-largest film distributor in China, with 2.26% of the market.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://english.entgroup.cn/uploads/reports/China%20Film%20Industry%20Report%202014-2015%EF%BC%88in%20brief%EF%BC%89.pdf|title= China Film Industry Report 2014-2015 (In Brief)|accessdate= October 15, 2015|work= english.entgroup.cn|publisher= EntGroup Inc}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe company was founded in 1994 as a film production company. It underwent a comprehensive expansion into the media industry through investing and now produces movies, TV shows, & music and operates a film studio, TV production company, a talent agency, a record label, and movie theaters.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.trmusic.com.cn/intro/about.htm |title=www.trmusic.com.cn/intro/about.htm |access-date=2010-12-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110901230544/http://www.trmusic.com.cn/intro/about.htm |archive-date=2011-09-01 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\nIn February 2011, Huayi Brothers revealed their plans to create the largest TV and film studio complex in East Asia.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://asiapacificarts.usc.edu/article@apa?huayi_brothers_to_build_east_asias_largest_film_and_tv_studio_complex_16432.aspx | title = Huayi Brothers to build East Asia's largest film and TV studio complex | publisher = Asia Pacific Arts | date = 2011-02-24 | access-date = 2011-02-26 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140413131510/http://asiapacificarts.usc.edu/article@apa?huayi_brothers_to_build_east_asias_largest_film_and_tv_studio_complex_16432.aspx | archive-date = 2014-04-13 | url-status = dead }}</ref> Also, they announced that they aim to earn 10 billion yuan in the box office by 2016.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://asiapacificarts.usc.edu/article@apa?huayi_brothers_unveils_their_moneymaking_plan_16522.aspx | title = Huayi Brothers unveils their moneymaking plan | publisher = Asia Pacific Arts | date = 2011-03-16 | access-date = 2011-03-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170826065207/http://asiapacificarts.usc.edu/article@apa?huayi_brothers_unveils_their_moneymaking_plan_16522.aspx | archive-date = 2017-08-26 | url-status = dead }}</ref> As of April 2015, the company was worth US$7.9 billion.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://variety.com/2015/biz/asia/chinese-media-stocks-stage-major-rally-in-us-and-asian-markets-1201469237/|title= Chinese Media Stocks Stage Major Rally in U.S. and Asian Markets|author= Patrick Frater|date= April 9, 2015|accessdate= April 14, 2015|work=[[variety.com]]}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014 the company announced that it had agreed to invest as much as $150 million in Studio 8, the production company launched by former [[Warner Bros.]] executive Jeff Robinov, but Shanghai-based conglomerate [[Fosun International]] later signed a deal to invest in Robinov's company instead.<ref>Verrier, Richard [http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/cotown/la-et-ct-china-broken-deals-20150906-story.html For Hollywood, the road to China is littered with broken deals] ''Los Angeles Times''. September 7, 2015</ref> The same year the company acquired 79% stake<ref>https://technology.ihs.com/511196/huayi-brothers-to-acquire-leading-stake-in-gdc-technology</ref><ref>https://variety.com/2014/biz/asia/chinas-huayi-to-pay-125-million-for-d-cinema-group-gdc-technology-1201307397/</ref><ref>https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/chinas-huayi-brothers-buys-controlling-733146</ref><ref>http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2014-09/17/content_18614620.htm</ref> in GDC Technology Limited, a ''[[Digital cinema|Digital Cinema]]'' solutions provider,  which was held by private equity funds ''[[The Carlyle Group|Carlyle Group]]'' and Yunfeng Capital.<ref>https://www.carlyle.com/our-business/portfolio-of-investments/gdc-technology-limited</ref><ref>https://www.carlyle.com/media-room/news-release-archive/carlyle-led-consortium-acquires-80-stake-gdc-technology</ref><ref>https://www.reuters.com/article/carlyle-cinema-idUKL3E7LH0CC20111017?type=companyNews</ref>\n\n==Artists==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Angelababy]]\n*[[Duan Yihong]]\n*[[Fei (singer)|Fei]]\n*[[Feng Shaofeng]]\n*[[Pace Wu]]\n*[[Li Bing Bing]]\n*[[Lu Ning]] \n*[[He Zhuoyan]]\n*[[Zhao Liying]] \n*[[Zhou Xun]]\n*[[Yao Chen]]\n*[[Wang Luoyong]]\n*[[Vision Wei Chen]]\n{{colend}}\n\n==Productions==\n===TV series===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! English Title\n! Alternative Title\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Episodes\n|-\n|2006\n| ''Soldiers Sortie''\n| \u58eb\u5175\u7a